{"_id":"FbJ2DzcSNgBI5KU8","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"burning incense for air, soft clay for earth, sulfur and phosphorus for fire, or water and sand for water","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You call forth an elemental servant. Choose an area of air, earth, fire, or water that fills a 10-foot cube within range. An elemental of challenge rating 5 or lower appropriate to the area you chose appears in an unoccupied space within 10 feet of it. For example, a fire elemental emerges from a bonfire, and an earth elemental rises up from the ground. The elemental disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The elemental is friendly to you and your companions for the duration. Roll initiative for the elemental, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal commands that you issue to it (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to the elemental, it defends itself from hostile creatures but otherwise takes no actions.</p>\n<p>If your concentration is broken, the elemental doesn't disappear. Instead, you lose control of the elemental, it becomes hostile toward you and your companions, and it might attack. An uncontrolled elemental can't be dismissed by you, and it disappears 1 hour after you summoned it.</p>\n<p>The GM has the elemental's statistics. Sample elementals can be found below.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level above 5th.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Sample Elementals</strong></p>\n<table class=\"summoning-creatures-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>CR</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Creature Name</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1/4</strong></td>\n<td>Steam Mephit</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1/2</strong></td>\n<td>Dust Mephit, Ice Mephit, Magma Mephit, Magmin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2</strong></td>\n<td>Azer, Gargoyle</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>5</strong></td>\n<td>Air Elemental, Earth Elemental, Fire Elemental, Salamander, Water Elemental, Xorn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>6</strong></td>\n<td>Invisible Stalker</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You call forth an elemental servant. Choose an area of air, earth, fire, or water that fills a 10-foot cube within range. An elemental of challenge rating 5 or lower appropriate to the area you chose appears in an unoccupied space within 10 feet of it. For example, a fire elemental emerges from a bonfire, and an earth elemental rises up from the ground. The elemental disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The elemental is friendly to you and your companions for the duration. Roll initiative for the elemental, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal commands that you issue to it (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to the elemental, it defends itself from hostile creatures but otherwise takes no actions.</p>\n<p>If your concentration is broken, the elemental doesn't disappear. Instead, you lose control of the elemental, it becomes hostile toward you and your companions, and it might attack. An uncontrolled elemental can't be dismissed by you, and it disappears 1 hour after you summoned it.</p>\n<p>The GM has the elemental's statistics. Sample elementals can be found below.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level above 5th.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Sample Elementals</strong></p>\n<table class=\"summoning-creatures-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th><strong>CR</strong></th>\n<th><strong>Creature Name</strong></th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1/4</strong></td>\n<td>Steam Mephit</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>1/2</strong></td>\n<td>Dust Mephit, Ice Mephit, Magma Mephit, Magmin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>2</strong></td>\n<td>Azer, Gargoyle</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>5</strong></td>\n<td>Air Elemental, Earth Elemental, Fire Elemental, Salamander, Water Elemental, Xorn</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>6</strong></td>\n<td>Invisible Stalker</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"burning incense for air, soft clay for earth, sulfur and phosphorus for fire, or water and sand for water"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":90},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 225","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.bQo8KDyAnn2heEYi"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2041,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136275,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":225,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange.webp","name":"Conjure Elemental","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"FcZXSlMDiChw9Lhf","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You attempt to compel a creature into a duel. One creature that you can see within range must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is drawn to you, compelled by your divine demand. For the duration, it has disadvantage on attack rolls against creatures other than you, and must make a Wisdom saving throw each time it attempts to move to a space that is more than 30 feet away from you; if it succeeds on this saving throw, this spell doesn’t restrict the target’s movement for that turn. <br /><br />The spell ends if you attack any other creature, if you cast a spell that targets a hostile creature other than the target, if a creature friendly to you damages the target or casts a harmful spell on it, or if you end your turn more than 30 feet away from the target.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You attempt to compel a creature into a duel. One creature that you can see within range must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is drawn to you, compelled by your divine demand. For the duration, it has disadvantage on attack rolls against creatures other than you, and must make a Wisdom saving throw each time it attempts to move to a space that is more than 30 feet away from you; if it succeeds on this saving throw, this spell doesn’t restrict the target’s movement for that turn. <br /><br />The spell ends if you attack any other creature, if you cast a spell that targets a hostile creature other than the target, if a creature friendly to you damages the target or casts a harmful spell on it, or if you end your turn more than 30 feet away from the target.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"enc","source":"Player's Handbook pg 224","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.kmhGPx61TrDMqgSt"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2313,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136243,"sources":[{"pageNumber":224,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Social","Debuff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/skills/melee/weapons-crossed-swords-white-blue.webp","name":"Compelled Duel","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"FpN6pnfZXQ2PQFtk","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a drop of water if creating water or a few grains of sand if destroying it","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You either create or destroy water.</p>\n<p><strong>Create Water.</strong> You create up to 10 gallons of clean water within range in an open container. Alternatively, the water falls as rain in a 30-foot cube within range, extinguishing exposed flames in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Destroy Water.</strong> You destroy up to 10 gallons of water in an open container within range. Alternatively, you destroy fog in a 30-foot cube within range.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you create or destroy 10 additional gallons of water, or the size of the cube increases by 5 feet, for each slot level above 1st.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You either create or destroy water.</p>\n<p><strong>Create Water.</strong> You create up to 10 gallons of clean water within range in an open container. Alternatively, the water falls as rain in a 30-foot cube within range, extinguishing exposed flames in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Destroy Water.</strong> You destroy up to 10 gallons of water in an open container within range. Alternatively, you destroy fog in a 30-foot cube within range.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you create or destroy 10 additional gallons of water, or the size of the cube increases by 5 feet, for each slot level above 1st.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a dro