{"_id":"QTYxAVwAStyxTWZs","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"rsak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d6","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A flash of light streaks toward a creature of your choice within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 4d6 radiant damage, and the next attack roll made against this target before the end of your next turn has advantage, thanks to the mystical dim light glittering on the target until then.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A flash of light streaks toward a creature of your choice within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 4d6 radiant damage, and the next attack roll made against this target before the end of your next turn has advantage, thanks to the mystical dim light glittering on the target until then.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"round","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"level"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 248","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.B2QIeuuw30mQqPej"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2133,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138023,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":248,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Buff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/fire/projectile-fireball-smoke-large-blue.webp","name":"Guiding Bolt","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QYusSuVpe69UJd3A","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a vial of quicksilver worth 500 gp and a life-sized human doll, both of which the spell consumes, and an intricate crystal rod worth at least 1,500 gp that is not consumed","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>While casting the spell, you place a vial of quicksilver in the chest of a life-sized human doll stuffed with ash or dust. You then stitch up the doll and drip your blood on it. At the end of the casting, you tap the doll with a crystal rod, transforming it into a magen clothed in whatever the doll was wearing. The type of magen is chosen by you during the casting of the spell. See <a style=\"color:#47d18c\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/idrotf/appendix-c-creatures#Magen\">appendix C</a> for different kinds of magen and their statistics.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Demos Magen</li>\n<li>Galvan Magen</li>\n<li>Hypnos Magen</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When the magen appears, your hit point maximum decreases by an amount equal to the magen’s challenge rating (minimum reduction of 1). Only a wish spell can undo this reduction to your hit point maximum.</p>\n<p>Any magen you create with this spell obeys your commands without question.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>While casting the spell, you place a vial of quicksilver in the chest of a life-sized human doll stuffed with ash or dust. You then stitch up the doll and drip your blood on it. At the end of the casting, you tap the doll with a crystal rod, transforming it into a magen clothed in whatever the doll was wearing. The type of magen is chosen by you during the casting of the spell. See <a style=\"color:#47d18c\" href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/idrotf/appendix-c-creatures#Magen\">appendix C</a> for different kinds of magen and their statistics.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Demos Magen</li>\n<li>Galvan Magen</li>\n<li>Hypnos Magen</li>\n</ul>\n<p>When the magen appears, your hit point maximum decreases by an amount equal to the magen’s challenge rating (minimum reduction of 1). Only a wish spell can undo this reduction to your hit point maximum.</p>\n<p>Any magen you create with this spell obeys your commands without question.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":500,"supply":0,"value":"a vial of quicksilver worth 500 gp and a life-sized human doll, both of which the spell consumes, and an intricate crystal rod worth at least 1,500 gp that is not consumed"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden pg 318","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.4zIkltBuAkYQVewy"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":654073,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":5322315,"sources":[{"pageNumber":318,"sourceId":66,"sourceType":1}],"tags":[]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/commodities/treasure/doll-voodoo.webp","name":"Create Magen","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QZTcdZLFIhkw1tvO","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a pickled octopus tentacle","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","cold"],["2d6","acid"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You open a gateway to the dark between the stars, a region infested with unknown horrors. A 20-foot-radius sphere of blackness and bitter cold appears, centered on a point with range and lasting for the duration. This void is filled with a cacophony of soft whispers and slurping noises that can be heard up to 30 feet away. No light, magical or otherwise, can illuminate the area, and creatures fully within the area are blinded.<br /><br />The void creates a warp in the fabric of space, and the area is difficult terrain. Any creature that starts its turn in the area takes 2d6 cold damage. Any creature that ends its turn in the area must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 2d6 acid damage as milky, otherworldly tentacles rub against it.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You open a gateway to the dark between the stars, a region infested with unknown horrors. A 20-foot-radius sphere of blackness and bitter cold appears, centered on a point with range and lasting for the duration. This void is filled with a cacophony of soft whispers and slurping noises that can be heard up to 30 feet away. No light, magical or otherwise, can illuminate the area, and creatures fully within the area are blinded.<br /><br />The void creates a warp in the fabric of space, and the area is difficult terrain. Any creature that starts its turn in the area takes 2d6 cold damage. Any creature that ends its turn in the area must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 2d6 acid damage as milky, otherworldly tentacles rub against it.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a pickled octopus tentacle"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":150},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Player's Handbook pg 251","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":20,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.tx0DaMOqQCnw9VRt"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2339,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":182567,"sources":[{"pageNumber":251,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/water/barrier-ice-shield.webp","name":"Hunger of Hadar","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QdyZQfP2xDXyd6jH","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":10,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a statuette of yourself carved from ivory and decorated with gems worth at least 1,500 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Choose a spell of 5th level or lower that you can cast, that has a casting time of 1 action, and that can target you. You cast that spell--called the contingent spell--as part of casting <strong>contingency</strong>, expending spell slots for both, but the contingent spell doesn't come into effect. Instead, it takes effect when a certain circumstance occurs. You describe that circumstance when you cast the two spells. For example, a <strong>contingency</strong> cast with water breathing might stipulate that breathing comes into effect when you are engulfed in water or a similar liquid.</p>\n<p>The contingent spell takes effect immediately after the circumstance is met for the first time, whether or not you want it to, and then <strong>contingency</strong> ends.</p>\n<p>The contingent spell takes effect only on you, even if it can normally target others. You can use only one <strong>contingency</strong> spell at a time.</p>\n<p>If you cast this spell again, the effect of another <strong>contingency</strong> spell on you ends. Also, <strong>contingency</strong> ends on you if its material component is ever not on your person.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Choose a spell of 5th level or lower that you can cast, that has a casting time of 1 action, and that can target you. You cast that spell--called the contingent spell--as part of casting <strong>contingency</strong>, expending spell slots for both, but the contingent spell doesn't come into effect. Instead, it takes effect when a certain circumstance occurs. You describe that circumstance when you cast the two spells. For example, a <strong>contingency</strong> cast with water breathing might stipulate that breathing comes into effect when you are engulfed in water or a similar liquid.</p>\n<p>The contingent spell takes effect immediately after the circumstance is met for the first time, whether or not you want it to, and then <strong>contingency</strong> ends.</p>\n<p>The contingent spell takes effect only on you, even if it can normally target others. You can use only one <strong>contingency</strong> spell at a time.</p>\n<p>If you cast this spell again, the effect of another <strong>contingency</strong> spell on you ends. Also, <strong>contingency</strong> ends on you if its material component is ever not on your person.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"day","value":10},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":1500,"supply":0,"value":"a statuette of yourself carved from ivory and decorated with gems worth at least 1,500 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 227","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.fToN05pXzlYiwfE0"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2047,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136300,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":227,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Utility"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-pentagon-teal-purple.webp","name":"Contingency","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QeicKNRhGGyCNMYJ","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"10 gp worth of charcoal, incense, and herbs that must be consumed by fire in a brass brazier","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You gain the service of a familiar, a spirit that takes an animal form you choose: bat, cat, crab, frog (toad), hawk, lizard, octopus, owl, poisonous snake, fish (quipper), rat, raven, sea horse, spider, or weasel. Appearing in an unoccupied space within range, the familiar has the statistics of the chosen form, though it is a celestial, fey, or fiend (your choice) instead of a beast.</p>\n<p>Your familiar acts independently of you, but it always obeys your commands. In combat, it rolls its own initiative and acts on its own turn. A familiar can't attack, but it can take other actions as normal.</p>\n<p>When the familiar drops to 0 hit points, it disappears, leaving behind no physical form. It reappears after you cast this spell again.</p>\n<p>While your familiar is within 100 feet of you, you can communicate with it telepathically. Additionally, as an action, you can see through your familiar's eyes and hear what it hears until the start of your next turn, gaining the benefits of any special senses that the familiar has. During this time, you are deaf and blind with regard to your own senses.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can temporarily dismiss your familiar. It disappears into a pocket dimension where it awaits your summons. Alternatively, you can dismiss it forever. As an action while it is temporarily dismissed, you can cause it to reappear in any unoccupied space within 30 feet of you.</p>\n<p>You can't have more than one familiar at a time. If you cast this spell while you already have a familiar, you instead cause it to adopt a new form. Choose one of the forms from the above list. Your familiar transforms into the chosen creature.</p>\n<p>Finally, when you cast a spell with a range of touch, your familiar can deliver the spell as if it had cast the spell. Your familiar must be within 100 feet of you, and it must use its reaction to deliver the spell when you cast it. If the spell requires an attack roll, you use your attack modifier for the roll.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You gain the service of a familiar, a spirit that takes an animal form you choose: bat, cat, crab, frog (toad), hawk, lizard, octopus, owl, poisonous snake, fish (quipper), rat, raven, sea horse, spider, or weasel. Appearing in an unoccupied space within range, the familiar has the statistics of the chosen form, though it is a celestial, fey, or fiend (your choice) instead of a beast.</p>\n<p>Your familiar acts independently of you, but it always obeys your commands. In combat, it rolls its own initiative and acts on its own turn. A familiar can't attack, but it can take other actions as normal.</p>\n<p>When the familiar drops to 0 hit points, it disappears, leaving behind no physical form. It reappears after you cast this spell again.</p>\n<p>While your familiar is within 100 feet of you, you can communicate with it telepathically. Additionally, as an action, you can see through your familiar's eyes and hear what it hears until the start of your next turn, gaining the benefits of any special senses that the familiar has. During this time, you are deaf and blind with regard to your own senses.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can temporarily dismiss your familiar. It disappears into a pocket dimension where it awaits your summons. Alternatively, you can dismiss it forever. As an action while it is temporarily dismissed, you can cause it to reappear in any unoccupied space within 30 feet of you.</p>\n<p>You can't have more than one familiar at a time. If you cast this spell while you already have a familiar, you instead cause it to adopt a new form. Choose one of the forms from the above list. Your familiar transforms into the chosen creature.</p>\n<p>Finally, when you cast a spell with a range of touch, your familiar can deliver the spell as if it had cast the spell. Your familiar must be within 100 feet of you, and it must use its reaction to deliver the spell when you cast it. If the spell requires an attack roll, you use your attack modifier for the roll.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":10,"supply":0,"value":"10 gp worth of charcoal, incense, and herbs that must be consumed by fire in a brass brazier"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":10},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 240","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.5g2sz6twIYwe99BY"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2097,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136790,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":240,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/wolf-paw-glow-purple-teal.webp","name":"Find Familiar","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QrmomIhMhpOz71Px","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a handful of sand, a dab of ink, and a writing quill plucked from a sleeping bird","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>This spell shapes a creature's dreams. Choose a creature known to you as the target of this spell. The target must be on the same plane of existence as you. Creatures that don't sleep, such as elves, can't be contacted by this spell. You, or a willing creature you touch, enters a trance state, acting as a messenger. While in the trance, the messenger is aware of his or her surroundings, but can't take actions or move.</p>\n<p>If the target is asleep, the messenger appears in the target's dreams and can converse with the target as long as it remains asleep, through the duration of the spell. The messenger can also shape the environment of the dream, creating landscapes, objects, and other images. The messenger can emerge from the trance at any time, ending the effect of the spell early. The target recalls the dream perfectly upon waking. If the target is awake when you cast the spell, the messenger knows it, and can either end the trance (and the spell) or wait for the target to fall asleep, at which point the messenger appears in the target's dreams.</p>\n<p>You can make the messenger appear monstrous and terrifying to the target. If you do, the messenger can deliver a message of no more than ten words and then the target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, echoes of the phantasmal monstrosity spawn a nightmare that lasts the duration of the target's sleep and prevents the target from gaining any benefit from that rest. In addition, when the target wakes up, it takes 3d6 psychic damage.</p>\n<p>If you have a body part, lock of hair, clipping from a nail, or similar portion of the target's body, the target makes its saving throw with disadvantage.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>This spell shapes a creature's dreams. Choose a creature known to you as the target of this spell. The target must be on the same plane of existence as you. Creatures that don't sleep, such as elves, can't be contacted by this spell. You, or a willing creature you touch, enters a trance state, acting as a messenger. While in the trance, the messenger is aware of his or her surroundings, but can't take actions or move.</p>\n<p>If the target is asleep, the messenger appears in the target's dreams and can converse with the target as long as it remains asleep, through the duration of the spell. The messenger can also shape the environment of the dream, creating landscapes, objects, and other images. The messenger can emerge from the trance at any time, ending the effect of the spell early. The target recalls the dream perfectly upon waking. If the target is awake when you cast the spell, the messenger knows it, and can either end the trance (and the spell) or wait for the target to fall asleep, at which point the messenger appears in the target's dreams.</p>\n<p>You can make the messenger appear monstrous and terrifying to the target. If you do, the messenger can deliver a message of no more than ten words and then the target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, echoes of the phantasmal monstrosity spawn a nightmare that lasts the duration of the target's sleep and prevents the target from gaining any benefit from that rest. In addition, when the target wakes up, it takes 3d6 psychic damage.</p>\n<p>If you have a body part, lock of hair, clipping from a nail, or similar portion of the target's body, the target makes its saving throw with disadvantage.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":8},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a handful of sand, a dab of ink, and a writing quill plucked from a sleeping bird"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 236","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.A1WvmSCWWs1MYRSG"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2079,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136698,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":236,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Communication"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-swirling-pink.webp","name":"Dream","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"Quzl8n2oEmdi75SP","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A tendril of inky darkness reaches out from you, touching a creature you can see within range to drain life from it. The target must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a successful save, the target takes 2d8 necrotic damage, and the spell ends. On a failed save, the target takes 4d8 necrotic damage, and until the spell ends, you can use your action on each of your turns to automatically deal 4d8 necrotic damage to the target. The spell ends if you use your action to do anything else, if the target is ever outside the spell’s range, or if the target has total cover from you.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Whenever the spell deals damage to a target, you regain hit points equal to half the amount of necrotic damage the target takes.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A tendril of inky darkness reaches out from you, touching a creature you can see within range to drain life from it. The target must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a successful save, the target takes 2d8 necrotic damage, and the spell ends. On a failed save, the target takes 4d8 necrotic damage, and until the spell ends, you can use your action on each of your turns to automatically deal 4d8 necrotic damage to the target. The spell ends if you use your action to do anything else, if the target is ever outside the spell’s range, or if the target has total cover from you.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Whenever the spell deals damage to a target, you regain hit points equal to half the amount of necrotic damage the target takes.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 155","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.N3bLHnMwgGhwSwzH"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14869,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138090,"sources":[{"pageNumber":155,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Healing","Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/commodities/biological/eye-tentacle-grey-orange.webp","name":"Enervation","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"QvU4udMh3x18kacH","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"heal","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8 + @mod","healing"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A wave of healing energy washes out from a point of your choice within range. Choose up to six creatures in a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on that point. Each target regains hit points equal to 3d8 + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels. </strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the healing increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A wave of healing energy washes out from a point of your choice within range. Choose up to six creatures in a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on that point. Each target regains hit points equal to 3d8 + your spellcasting ability modifier. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels. </strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the healing increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d8","mode":"level"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 258","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":30,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.eOH9gPUwliW8lfuI"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2181,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138459,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":258,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Healing"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/life/heart-cross-strong-green.webp","name":"Mass Cure Wounds","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"R1cO1iI8PhxfZSGN","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You utter a divine word, imbued with the power that shaped the world at the dawn of creation. Choose any number of creatures you can see within range. Each creature that can hear you must make a Charisma saving throw. On a failed save, a creature suffers an effect based on its current hit points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>50 hit points or fewer: deafened for 1 minute</li>\n<li>40 hit points or fewer: deafened and blinded for 10 minutes</li>\n<li>30 hit points or fewer: blinded, deafened, and stunned for 1 hour</li>\n<li>20 hit points or fewer: killed instantly</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />Regardless of its current hit points, a celestial, an elemental, a fey, or a fiend that fails its save is forced back to its plane of origin (if it isn't there already) and can't return to your current plane for 24 hours by any means short of a <strong>wish</strong> spell.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You utter a divine word, imbued with the power that shaped the world at the dawn of creation. Choose any number of creatures you can see within range. Each creature that can hear you must make a Charisma saving throw. On a failed save, a creature suffers an effect based on its current hit points:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>50 hit points or fewer: deafened for 1 minute</li>\n<li>40 hit points or fewer: deafened and blinded for 10 minutes</li>\n<li>30 hit points or fewer: blinded, deafened, and stunned for 1 hour</li>\n<li>20 hit points or fewer: killed instantly</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />Regardless of its current hit points, a celestial, an elemental, a fey, or a fiend that fails its save is forced back to its plane of origin (if it isn't there already) and can't return to your current plane for 24 hours by any means short of a <strong>wish</strong> spell.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 234","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.qUnrdcN66jy2tOY9"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2075,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136646,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":234,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Debuff","Banishment"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-large-orange-purple.webp","name":"Divine Word","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"RQDt2ieBQUNJyQJh","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"bat fur and a drop of pitch or piece of coal","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Magical darkness spreads from a point you choose within range to fill a 15-foot-radius sphere for the duration. The darkness spreads around corners. A creature with darkvision can't see through this darkness, and nonmagical light can't illuminate it.</p>\n<p>If the point you choose is on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the darkness emanates from the object and moves with it. Completely covering the source of the darkness with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the darkness.</p>\n<p>If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of light created by a spell of 2nd level or lower, the spell that created the light is dispelled.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Magical darkness spreads from a point you choose within range to fill a 15-foot-radius sphere for the duration. The darkness spreads around corners. A creature with darkvision can't see through this darkness, and nonmagical light can't illuminate it.</p>\n<p>If the point you choose is on an object you are holding or one that isn't being worn or carried, the darkness emanates from the object and moves with it. Completely covering the source of the darkness with an opaque object, such as a bowl or a helm, blocks the darkness.</p>\n<p>If any of this spell's area overlaps with an area of light created by a spell of 2nd level or lower, the spell that created the light is dispelled.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"bat fur and a drop of pitch or 