{"_id":"TUs5aQovknCEUBaV","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"rsak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A black beam of enervating energy springs from your finger toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target deals only half damage with weapon attacks that use Strength until the spell ends.</p>\n<p>At the end of each of the target's turns, it can make a Constitution saving throw against the spell. On a success, the spell ends.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A black beam of enervating energy springs from your finger toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target deals only half damage with weapon attacks that use Strength until the spell ends.</p>\n<p>At the end of each of the target's turns, it can make a Constitution saving throw against the spell. On a success, the spell ends.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 271","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.dKgAzPV3cPcj0Ypp"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2225,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138631,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":271,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Debuff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/beam-rays-teal.webp","name":"Ray of Enfeeblement","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ThrTRzz6KflrfjE3","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"ruby dust worth 1,500 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>An immobile, invisible, cube-shaped prison composed of magical force springs into existence around an area you choose within range. The prison can be a cage or a solid box, as you choose.</p>\n<p>A prison in the shape of a cage can be up to 20 feet on a side and is made from 1/2-inch diameter bars spaced 1/2 inch apart.</p>\n<p>A prison in the shape of a box can be up to 10 feet on a side, creating a solid barrier that prevents any matter from passing through it and blocking any spells cast into or out from the area.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell, any creature that is completely inside the cage's area is trapped. Creatures only partially within the area, or those too large to fit inside the area, are pushed away from the center of the area until they are completely outside the area.</p>\n<p>A creature inside the cage can't leave it by nonmagical means. If the creature tries to use teleportation or interplanar travel to leave the cage, it must first make a Charisma saving throw. On a success, the creature can use that magic to exit the cage. On a failure, the creature can't exit the cage and wastes the use of the spell or effect. The cage also extends into the Ethereal Plane, blocking ethereal travel.</p>\n<p>This spell can't be dispelled by <strong>dispel magic</strong>.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>An immobile, invisible, cube-shaped prison composed of magical force springs into existence around an area you choose within range. The prison can be a cage or a solid box, as you choose.</p>\n<p>A prison in the shape of a cage can be up to 20 feet on a side and is made from 1/2-inch diameter bars spaced 1/2 inch apart.</p>\n<p>A prison in the shape of a box can be up to 10 feet on a side, creating a solid barrier that prevents any matter from passing through it and blocking any spells cast into or out from the area.</p>\n<p>When you cast the spell, any creature that is completely inside the cage's area is trapped. Creatures only partially within the area, or those too large to fit inside the area, are pushed away from the center of the area until they are completely outside the area.</p>\n<p>A creature inside the cage can't leave it by nonmagical means. If the creature tries to use teleportation or interplanar travel to leave the cage, it must first make a Charisma saving throw. On a success, the creature can use that magic to exit the cage. On a failure, the creature can't exit the cage and wastes the use of the spell or effect. The cage also extends into the Ethereal Plane, blocking ethereal travel.</p>\n<p>This spell can't be dispelled by <strong>dispel magic</strong>.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":1500,"supply":0,"value":"ruby dust worth 1,500 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":100},"save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 243","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.Wx9Zyp1Qsid9ZS6i"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2114,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137879,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":243,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Warding"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-chains-ropes-net-purple-blue.webp","name":"Forcecage","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"Ts95sgprueITE06D","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"fire and holy water","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You and up to ten willing creatures you can see within range assume a gaseous form for the duration, appearing as wisps of cloud. While in this cloud form, a creature has a flying speed of 300 feet and has resistance to damage from nonmagical weapons. The only actions a creature can take in this form are the Dash action or to revert to its normal form. Reverting takes 1 minute, during which time a creature is incapacitated and can't move. Until the spell ends, a creature can revert to cloud form, which also requires the 1-minute transformation.</p>\n<p>If a creature is in cloud form and flying when the effect ends, the creature descends 60 feet per round for 1 minute until it lands, which it does safely. If it can't land after 1 minute, the creature falls the remaining distance.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You and up to ten willing creatures you can see within range assume a gaseous form for the duration, appearing as wisps of cloud. While in this cloud form, a creature has a flying speed of 300 feet and has resistance to damage from nonmagical weapons. The only actions a creature can take in this form are the Dash action or to revert to its normal form. Reverting takes 1 minute, during which time a creature is incapacitated and can't move. Until the spell ends, a creature can revert to cloud form, which also requires the 1-minute transformation.</p>\n<p>If a creature is in cloud form and flying when the effect ends, the creature descends 60 feet per round for 1 minute until it lands, which it does safely. If it can't land after 1 minute, the creature falls the remaining distance.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":8},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"fire and holy water"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 288","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":10,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.dNxpDY75EGqjeqqq"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2301,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138947,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":288,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff","Movement"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/wind-swirl-gray-blue.webp","name":"Wind Walk","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"TwBeI7CQbh5wL5Rv","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a holy symbol","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","radiant"],["3d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You call forth spirits to protect you. They flit around you to a distance of 15 feet for the duration. If you are good or neutral, their spectral form appears angelic or fey (your choice). If you are evil, they appear fiendish.</p>\n<p>When you cast this spell, you can designate any number of creatures you can see to be unaffected by it. An affected creature's speed is halved in the area, and when the creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 3d8 radiant damage (if you are good or neutral) or 3d8 necrotic damage (if you are evil). On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 3rd.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You call forth spirits to protect you. They flit around you to a distance of 15 feet for the duration. If you are good or neutral, their spectral form appears angelic or fey (your choice). If you are evil, they appear fiendish.</p>\n<p>When you cast this spell, you can designate any number of creatures you can see to be unaffected by it. An affected creature's speed is halved in the area, and when the creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 3d8 radiant damage (if you are good or neutral) or 3d8 necrotic damage (if you are evil). On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 3rd.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a holy symbol"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d8","mode":"level"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 278","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":15,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.5K61b1qPIJ7QegKS"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2264,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138784,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":278,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-bolts-salvo-white.webp","name":"Spirit Guardians","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"U0J4YNqUWitiQdvS","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"msak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a bit of phosphorus or a firefly","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","fire"],["2d8","cold"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Thin and wispy flames wreathe your body for the duration, shedding bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. You can end the spell early by using an action to dismiss it.</p>\n<p>The flames provide you with a warm shield or a chill shield, as you choose. The warm shield grants you resistance to cold damage, and the chill shield grants you resistance to fire damage.</p>\n<p>In addition, whenever a creature within 5 feet of you hits you with a melee attack, the shield erupts with flame. The attacker takes 2d8 fire damage from a warm shield, or 2d8 cold damage from a cold shield.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Thin and wispy flames wreathe your body for the duration, shedding bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. You can end the spell early by using an action to dismiss it.</p>\n<p>The flames provide you with a warm shield or a chill shield, as you choose. The warm shield grants you resistance to cold damage, and the chill shield grants you resistance to fire damage.</p>\n<p>In addition, whenever a creature within 5 feet of you hits you with a melee attack, the shield erupts with flame. The attacker takes 2d8 fire damage from a warm shield, or 2d8 cold damage from a cold shield.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a bit of phosphorus or a firefly"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 242","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.QPm5H1zLasI6vMSw"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2104,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136891,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":242,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Buff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-pentagon-red.webp","name":"Fire Shield","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"U3HfebZU41aBAl4d","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a bit of fleece and jade dust worth at least 25 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create an illusion of an object, a creature, or some other visible phenomenon within range that activates when a specific condition occurs. The illusion is imperceptible until then. It must be no larger than a 30-foot cube, and you decide when you cast the spell how the illusion behaves and what sounds it makes. This scripted performance can last up to 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>When the condition you specify occurs, the illusion springs into existence and performs in the manner you described. Once the illusion finishes performing, it disappears and remains dormant for 10 minutes. After this time, the illusion can be activated again.</p>\n<p>The triggering condition can be as general or as detailed as you like, though it must be based on visual or audible conditions that occur within 30 feet of the area. For example, you could create an illusion of yourself to appear and warn off others who attempt to open a trapped door, or you could set the illusion to trigger only when a creature says the correct word or phrase.</p>\n<p>Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. A creature that uses its action to examine the image can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the creature can see through the image, and any noise it makes sounds hollow to the creature.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create an illusion of an object, a creature, or some other visible phenomenon within range that activates when a specific condition occurs. The illusion is imperceptible until then. It must be no larger than a 30-foot cube, and you decide when you cast the spell how the illusion behaves and what sounds it makes. This scripted performance can last up to 5 minutes.</p>\n<p>When the condition you specify occurs, the illusion springs into existence and performs in the manner you described. Once the illusion finishes performing, it disappears and remains dormant for 10 minutes. After this time, the illusion can be activated again.</p>\n<p>The triggering condition can be as general or as detailed as you like, though it must be based on visual or audible conditions that occur within 30 feet of the area. For example, you could create an illusion of yourself to appear and warn off others who attempt to open a trapped door, or you could set the illusion to trigger only when a creature says the correct word or phrase.</p>\n<p>Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. A creature that uses its action to examine the image can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the creature can see through the image, and any noise it makes sounds hollow to the creature.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":25,"supply":0,"value":"a bit of fleece and jade dust worth at least 25 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 269","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":30,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.nfOnig8dD9fMgQde"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2218,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138598,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":269,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-chains-ropes-net-purple-blue.webp","name":"Programmed Illusion","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"UBPIRmzEX5Kg5g09","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A nature spirit answers your call and transforms you into a powerful guardian. The transformation lasts until the spell ends. You choose one of the following forms to assume: Primal Beast or Great Tree.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Primal Beast.</span></strong> Bestial fur covers your body, your facial features become feral, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">Your walking speed increases by 10 feet.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You gain darkvision with a range of 120 feet.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Strength-based attack rolls with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">Your melee weapon attacks deal an extra 1d6 force damage on a hit.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Great Tree.</span></strong> Your skin appears barky, leaves sprout from your hair, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You gain 10 temporary hit points.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Constitution saving throws with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Dexterity- and Wisdom-based attack rolls with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">While you are on the ground, the ground within 15 feet of you is difficult terrain for your enemies.</li>\n</ul>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A nature spirit answers your call and transforms you into a powerful guardian. The transformation lasts until the spell ends. You choose one of the following forms to assume: Primal Beast or Great Tree.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Primal Beast.</span></strong> Bestial fur covers your body, your facial features become feral, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">Your walking speed increases by 10 feet.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You gain darkvision with a range of 120 feet.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Strength-based attack rolls with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">Your melee weapon attacks deal an extra 1d6 force damage on a hit.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Great Tree.</span></strong> Your skin appears barky, leaves sprout from your hair, and you gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You gain 10 temporary hit points.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Constitution saving throws with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">You make Dexterity- and Wisdom-based attack rolls with advantage.</li>\n<li class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Bulleted\">While you are on the ground, the ground within 15 feet of you is difficult terrain for your enemies.</li>\n</ul>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 157","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.sftMBOyxA235uvYO"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14872,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138108,"sources":[{"pageNumber":157,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff","Shapechanging"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/lotus-glow-pink.webp","name":"Guardian of Nature","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"US8t2T83pzmkP10c","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a glowing stick of incense or a crystal vial filled with phosphorescent material","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create a twisting pattern of colors that weaves through the air inside a 30-foot cube within range. The pattern appears for a moment and vanishes. Each creature in the area who sees the pattern must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature becomes charmed for the duration. While charmed by this spell, the creature is incapacitated and has a speed of 0.</p>\n<p>The spell ends for an affected creature if it takes any damage or if someone else uses an action to shake the creature out of its stupor.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create a twisting pattern of colors that weaves through the air inside a 30-foot cube within range. The pattern appears for a moment and vanishes. Each creature in the area who sees the pattern must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature becomes charmed for the duration. While charmed by this spell, the creature is incapacitated and has a speed of 0.</p>\n<p>The spell ends for an affected creature if it takes any damage or if someone else uses an action to shake the creature out of its stupor.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a glowing stick of incense or a crystal vial filled with phosphorescent material"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 252","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":30,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.iGMFRxRuksJfx44w"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2150,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138331,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":252,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/air-burst-spiral-pink.webp","name":"Hypnotic Pattern","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"UW4Y58NSJjvdV4ni","name":"Intellect Fortress","type":"spell","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-blue%20.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>For the duration, you or one willing creature you can see within range has resistance to psychic damage, as well as advantage on Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma saving throws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p>","chat":"<p>For the duration, you or one willing creature you can see within range has resistance to psychic damage, as well as advantage on Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma saving throws.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 3rd. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p>","unidentified":""},"source":"Tasha’s Cauldron of Everything pg 107","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":1,"units":"hour"},"target":{"value":1,"width":null,"units":"","type":"creature"},"range":{"value":30,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"util","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":3,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.DRAJV4zNdL7KRXD5"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":718549,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":5833334,"sources":[{"pageNumber":107,"sourceId":67,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff"]}}}
{"_id":"Ug6OQS0K3KGVjdZ7","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"incense and a vial of holy or unholy water","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You contact your deity or a divine proxy and ask up to three questions that can be answered with a yes or no. You must ask your questions before the spell ends. You receive a correct answer for each question.</p>\n<p>Divine beings aren't necessarily omniscient, so you might receive \"unclear\" as an answer if a question pertains to information that lies beyond the deity's knowledge. In a case where a one-word answer could be misleading or contrary to the deity's interests, the GM might offer a short phrase as an answer instead.</p>\n<p>If you cast the spell two or more times before finishing your next long rest, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get no answer. The GM makes this roll in secret.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You contact your deity or a divine proxy and ask up to three questions that can be answered with a yes or no. You must ask your questions before the spell ends. You receive a correct answer for each question.</p>\n<p>Divine beings aren't necessarily omniscient, so you might receive \"unclear\" as an answer if a question pertains to information that lies beyond the deity's knowledge. In a case where a one-word answer could be misleading or contrary to the deity's interests, the GM might offer a short phrase as an answer instead.</p>\n<p>If you cast the spell two or more times before finishing your next long rest, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get no answer. The GM makes this roll in secret.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"incense and a vial of holy or unholy water"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 223","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.TGf9nGbIuj7sU48Q"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2033,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136237,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":223,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Foreknowledge"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-energy-hold-levitate-blue-yellow.webp","name":"Commune","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"Uj0b2BclDZRgem2r","name":"Prismatic Wall","type":"spell","img":"icons/magic/light/beam-rays-orange-large.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>A shimmering, multicolored plane of light forms a vertical opaque wall--up to 90 feet long, 30 feet high, and 1 inch thick--centered on a point you can see within range. Alternatively, you can shape the wall into a sphere up to 30 feet in diameter centered on a point you choose within range. The wall remains in place for the duration. If you position the wall so that it passes through a space occupied by a creature, the spell fails, and your action and the spell slot are wasted.</p>\n<p>The wall sheds bright light out to a range of 100 feet and dim light for an additional 100 feet. You and creatures you designate at the time you cast the spell can pass through and remain near the wall without harm. If another creature that can see the wall moves to within 20 feet of it or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or become blinded for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>The wall consists of seven layers, each with a different color. When a creature attempts to reach into or pass through the wall, it does so one layer at a time through all the wall's layers. As it passes or reaches through each layer, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw or be affected by that layer's properties as described below.</p>\n<p>The wall can be destroyed, also one layer at a time, in order from red to violet, by means specific to each layer. Once a layer is destroyed, it remains so for the duration of the spell. <strong>Antimagic field</strong> has no effect on the wall, and <strong>dispel magic</strong> can affect only the violet layer.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Red.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. While this layer is in place, nonmagical ranged attacks can't pass through the wall. The layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 25 cold damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Orange.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. While this layer is in place, magical ranged attacks can't pass through the wall. The layer is destroyed by a strong wind.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Yellow.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 60 force damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Green.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A passwall spell, or another spell of equal or greater level that can open a portal on a solid surface, destroys this layer.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Blue.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 25 fire damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>6. Indigo.</strong> On a failed save, the creature is restrained. It must then make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If it successfully saves three times, the spell ends. If it fails its save three times, it permanently turns to stone and is subjected to the petrified condition. The successes and failures don't need to be consecutive; keep track of both until the creature collects three of a kind. While this layer is in place, spells can't be cast through the wall. The layer is destroyed by bright light shed by a <strong>daylight</strong> spell or a similar spell of equal or higher level.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Violet.</strong> On a failed save, the creature is blinded. It must then make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of your next turn. A successful save ends the blindness. If it fails that save, the creature is transported to another plane of the GM's choosing and is no longer blinded. (Typically, a creature that is on a plane that isn't its home plane is banished home, while other creatures are usually cast into the Astral or Ethereal planes.) This layer is destroyed by a <strong>dispel magic</strong> spell or a similar spell of equal or higher level that can end spells and magical effects.</p>","chat":"<p>A shimmering, multicolored plane of light forms a vertical opaque wall--up to 90 feet long, 30 feet high, and 1 inch thick--centered on a point you can see within range. Alternatively, you can shape the wall into a sphere up to 30 feet in diameter centered on a point you choose within range. The wall remains in place for the duration. If you position the wall so that it passes through a space occupied by a creature, the spell fails, and your action and the spell slot are wasted.</p>\n<p>The wall sheds bright light out to a range of 100 feet and dim light for an additional 100 feet. You and creatures you designate at the time you cast the spell can pass through and remain near the wall without harm. If another creature that can see the wall moves to within 20 feet of it or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or become blinded for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>The wall consists of seven layers, each with a different color. When a creature attempts to reach into or pass through the wall, it does so one layer at a time through all the wall's layers. As it passes or reaches through each layer, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw or be affected by that layer's properties as described below.</p>\n<p>The wall can be destroyed, also one layer at a time, in order from red to violet, by means specific to each layer. Once a layer is destroyed, it remains so for the duration of the spell. <strong>Antimagic field</strong> has no effect on the wall, and <strong>dispel magic</strong> can affect only the violet layer.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Red.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. While this layer is in place, nonmagical ranged attacks can't pass through the wall. The layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 25 cold damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Orange.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. While this layer is in place, magical ranged attacks can't pass through the wall. The layer is destroyed by a strong wind.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Yellow.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 60 force damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Green.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A passwall spell, or another spell of equal or greater level that can open a portal on a solid surface, destroys this layer.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Blue.</strong> The creature takes 10d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. This layer can be destroyed by dealing at least 25 fire damage to it.</p>\n<p><strong>6. Indigo.</strong> On a failed save, the creature is restrained. It must then make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If it successfully saves three times, the spell ends. If it fails its save three times, it permanently turns to stone and is subjected to the petrified condition. The successes and failures don't need to be consecutive; keep track of both until the creature collects three of a kind. While this layer is in place, spells can't be cast through the wall. The layer is destroyed by bright light shed by a <strong>daylight</strong> spell or a similar spell of equal or higher level.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Violet.</strong> On a failed save, the creature is blinded. It must then make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of your next turn. A successful save ends the blindness. If it fails that save, the creature is transported to another plane of the GM's choosing and is no longer blinded. (Typically, a creature that is on a plane that isn't its home plane is banished home, while other creatures are usually cast into the Astral or Ethereal planes.) This layer is destroyed by a <strong>dispel magic</strong> spell or a similar spell of equal or higher level that can end spells and magical effects.</p>","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 267","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":90,"width":null,"units":"ft","type":"wall"},"range":{"value":60,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","fire"],["10d6","acid"],["10d6","lightning"],["10d6","poison"],["10d6","cold"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":9,"school":"abj","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":false},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":"","1":"","2":"","3":"","4":""},"value":{"0":true,"1":true,"2":true,"3":true,"4":true}},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickTemplate":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.LgPJV1yie6QXqd7A"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2215,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138595,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":267,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}}}
{"_id":"UksMv2gbQvHZG5O8","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"tears inside a gem worth at least 300 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You call forth a shadowy spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Shadow Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose an emotion: Fury, Despair, or Fear. The creature resembles a misshapen biped marked by the chosen emotion, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder stat-block-background\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Shadow Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Medium monstrosity</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 11 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 35 + 15 for each spell level above 3rd</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 40 ft.</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">STR</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">13</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+1)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">DEX</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CON</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">15</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+2)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">INT</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">4</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">WIS</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">10</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CHA</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Damage Resistances </strong>necrotic</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Condition Immunities </strong>frightened</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Senses </strong>darkvision 120 ft., passive Perception 10</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Languages </strong>understands the languages you speak</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data-Last\"><strong>Challenge</strong> — <strong>Proficiency Bonus</strong> equals your bonus</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Terror Frenzy (Fury Only).</strong></em> The spirit has advantage on attack rolls against frightened creatures.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Weight of Sorrow (Despair Only).</strong></em> Any creature, other than you, that starts its turn within 5 feet of the spirit has its speed reduced by 20 feet until the start of that creature’s next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Multiattack.</strong></em> The spirit makes a number of attacks equal to half this spell’s level (rounded down).</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Chilling Rend.</strong></em> <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d12 + 3 + the spell’s level cold damage.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Dreadful Scream (1/Day).</strong></em> The spirit screams. Each creature within 30 feet of it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or be frightened of the spirit for 1 minute. The frightened creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Bonus Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Shadow Stealth (Fear Only).</strong></em> While in dim light or darkness, the spirit takes the Hide action.</p>\n</div>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You call forth a shadowy spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Shadow Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose an emotion: Fury, Despair, or Fear. The creature resembles a misshapen biped marked by the chosen emotion, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder stat-block-background\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Shadow Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Medium monstrosity</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 11 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 35 + 15 for each spell level above 3rd</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 40 ft.</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">STR</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">13</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+1)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">DEX</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CON</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">15</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+2)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">INT</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">4</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">WIS</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">10</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CHA</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Damage Resistances </strong>necrotic</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Condition Immunities </strong>frightened</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Senses </strong>darkvision 120 ft., passive Perception 10</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Languages </strong>understands the languages you speak</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data-Last\"><strong>Challenge</strong> — <strong>Proficiency Bonus</strong> equals your bonus</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Terror Frenzy (Fury Only).</strong></em> The spirit has advantage on attack rolls against frightened creatures.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Weight of Sorrow (Despair Only).</strong></em> Any creature, other than you, that starts its turn within 5 feet of the spirit has its speed reduced by 20 feet until the start of that creature’s next turn.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Multiattack.</strong></em> The spirit makes a number of attacks equal to half this spell’s level (rounded down).</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Chilling Rend.</strong></em> <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d12 + 3 + the spell’s level cold damage.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Dreadful Scream (1/Day).</strong></em> The spirit screams. Each creature within 30 feet of it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or be frightened of the spirit for 1 minute. The frightened creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Bonus Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Shadow Stealth (Fear Only).</strong></em> While in dim light or darkness, the spirit takes the Hide action.</p>\n</div>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":300,"supply":0,"value":"tears inside a gem worth at least 300 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":90},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Tasha’s Cauldron of Everything pg 113","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-sp