{"_id":"V4ZHGimi8xWn5xrq","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"fur or a feather from a beast","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You touch a creature and bestow upon it a magical enhancement. Choose one of the following effects; the target gains that effect until the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Bear's Endurance.</strong> The target has advantage on Constitution checks. It also gains 2d6 temporary hit points, which are lost when the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Bull's Strength.</strong> The target has advantage on Strength checks, and his or her carrying capacity doubles.</p>\n<p><strong>Cat's Grace.</strong> The target has advantage on Dexterity checks. It also doesn't take damage from falling 20 feet or less if it isn't incapacitated.</p>\n<p><strong>Eagle's Splendor.</strong> The target has advantage on Charisma checks.</p>\n<p><strong>Fox's Cunning.</strong> The target has advantage on Intelligence checks.</p>\n<p><strong>Owl's Wisdom.</strong> The target has advantage on Wisdom checks.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You touch a creature and bestow upon it a magical enhancement. Choose one of the following effects; the target gains that effect until the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Bear's Endurance.</strong> The target has advantage on Constitution checks. It also gains 2d6 temporary hit points, which are lost when the spell ends.</p>\n<p><strong>Bull's Strength.</strong> The target has advantage on Strength checks, and his or her carrying capacity doubles.</p>\n<p><strong>Cat's Grace.</strong> The target has advantage on Dexterity checks. It also doesn't take damage from falling 20 feet or less if it isn't incapacitated.</p>\n<p><strong>Eagle's Splendor.</strong> The target has advantage on Charisma checks.</p>\n<p><strong>Fox's Cunning.</strong> The target has advantage on Intelligence checks.</p>\n<p><strong>Owl's Wisdom.</strong> The target has advantage on Wisdom checks.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"fur or a feather from a beast"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 237","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.nRm4ogsMg2f9hCL5"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2083,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136709,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":237,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-flight-wings-runes-purple.webp","name":"Enhance Ability","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"V7vbP8HJvrAP52P2","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You choose nonmagical flame that you can see within range and that fits within a 5-foot cube. You affect it in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul id=\"l1\">\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously expand the flame 5 feet in one direction, provided that wood or other fuel is present in the new location.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously extinguish the flames within the cube.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You double or halve the area of bright light and dim light cast by the flame, change its color, or both. The change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You cause simple shapes—such as the vague form of a creature, an inanimate object, or a location—to appear within the flames and animate as you like. The shapes last for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You choose nonmagical flame that you can see within range and that fits within a 5-foot cube. You affect it in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul id=\"l1\">\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously expand the flame 5 feet in one direction, provided that wood or other fuel is present in the new location.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously extinguish the flames within the cube.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You double or halve the area of bright light and dim light cast by the flame, change its color, or both. The change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You cause simple shapes—such as the vague form of a creature, an inanimate object, or a location—to appear within the flames and animate as you like. The shapes last for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 152","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":5,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickTemplate":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.aRKUctBQwY0YNw2l"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2374,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137958,"sources":[{"pageNumber":152,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/sundries/lights/candles-lit-red-evil.webp","name":"Control Flames","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"VCAwjHeNOluPTTmE","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d8","poison"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of poisonous, yellow-green fog centered on a point you choose within range. The fog spreads around corners. It lasts for the duration or until strong wind disperses the fog, ending the spell. Its area is heavily obscured.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, that creature must make a Constitution saving throw. The creature takes 5d8 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Creatures are affected even if they hold their breath or don't need to breathe.</p>\n<p>The fog moves 10 feet away from you at the start of each of your turns, rolling along the surface of the ground. The vapors, being heavier than air, sink to the lowest level of the land, even pouring down openings.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of poisonous, yellow-green fog centered on a point you choose within range. The fog spreads around corners. It lasts for the duration or until strong wind disperses the fog, ending the spell. Its area is heavily obscured.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, that creature must make a Constitution saving throw. The creature takes 5d8 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Creatures are affected even if they hold their breath or don't need to breathe.</p>\n<p>The fog moves 10 feet away from you at the start of each of your turns, rolling along the surface of the ground. The vapors, being heavier than air, sink to the lowest level of the land, even pouring down openings.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 5th.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d8","mode":"level"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 222","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":20,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.TLtzB8spuZVs7t54"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2030,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136225,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":222,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-swirling-green.webp","name":"Cloudkill","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"VChgLTNMX8Dd46JU","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a vial of blood from a humanoid killed within the past 24 hours","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You utter foul words, summoning one demon from the chaos of the Abyss. You choose the demon’s type, which must be one of challenge rating 5 or lower, such as a shadow demon or a barlgura. The demon appears in an unoccupied space you can see within range, and the demon disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Roll initiative for the demon, which has its own turns. When you summon it and on each of your turns thereafter, you can issue a verbal command to it (requiring no action on your part), telling it what it must do on its next turn. If you issue no command, it spends its turn attacking any creature within reach that has attacked it.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">At the end of each of the demon’s turns, it makes a Charisma saving throw. The demon has disadvantage on this saving throw if you say its true name. On a failed save, the demon continues to obey you. On a successful save, your control of the demon ends for the rest of the duration, and the demon spends its turns pursuing and attacking the nearest non-demons to the best of its ability. If you stop concentrating on the spell before it reaches its full duration, an uncontrolled demon doesn’t disappear for 1d6 rounds if it still has hit points.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As part of casting the spell, you can form a circle on the ground with the blood used as a material component. The circle is large enough to encompass your space. While the spell lasts, the summoned demon can’t cross the circle or harm it, and it can’t target anyone within it. Using the material component in this manner consumes it when the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">At Higher Levels.</span></strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level above 4th.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You utter foul words, summoning one demon from the chaos of the Abyss. You choose the demon’s type, which must be one of challenge rating 5 or lower, such as a shadow demon or a barlgura. The demon appears in an unoccupied space you can see within range, and the demon disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Roll initiative for the demon, which has its own turns. When you summon it and on each of your turns thereafter, you can issue a verbal command to it (requiring no action on your part), telling it what it must do on its next turn. If you issue no command, it spends its turn attacking any creature within reach that has attacked it.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">At the end of each of the demon’s turns, it makes a Charisma saving throw. The demon has disadvantage on this saving throw if you say its true name. On a failed save, the demon continues to obey you. On a successful save, your control of the demon ends for the rest of the duration, and the demon spends its turns pursuing and attacking the nearest non-demons to the best of its ability. If you stop concentrating on the spell before it reaches its full duration, an uncontrolled demon doesn’t disappear for 1d6 rounds if it still has hit points.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As part of casting the spell, you can form a circle on the ground with the blood used as a material component. The circle is large enough to encompass your space. While the spell lasts, the summoned demon can’t cross the circle or harm it, and it can’t target anyone within it. Using the material component in this manner consumes it when the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">At Higher Levels.</span></strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level above 4th.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a vial of blood from a humanoid killed within the past 24 hours"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 166","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.rLu7XUjjLhfSzmCY"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14603,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138252,"sources":[{"pageNumber":166,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/fear-fright-monster-grin-green.webp","name":"Summon Greater Demon","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"VV0cOaDyKWUwefev","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":10,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You summon a spirit that assumes the form of an unusually intelligent, strong, and loyal steed, creating a long-lasting bond with it. Appearing in an unoccupied space within range, the steed takes on a form that you choose: a warhorse, a pony, a camel, an elk, or a mastiff. (Your GM might allow other animals to be summoned as steeds.) The steed has the statistics of the chosen form, though it is a celestial, fey, or fiend (your choice) instead of its normal type. Additionally, if your steed has an Intelligence of 5 or less, its Intelligence becomes 6, and it gains the ability to understand one language of your choice that you speak.</p>\n<p>Your steed serves you as a mount, both in combat and out, and you have an instinctive bond with it that allows you to fight as a seamless unit. While mounted on your steed, you can make any spell you cast that targets only you also target your steed.</p>\n<p>When the steed drops to 0 hit points, it disappears, leaving behind no physical form. You can also dismiss your steed at any time as an action, causing it to disappear. In either case, casting this spell again summons the same steed, restored to its hit point maximum.</p>\n<p>While your steed is within 1 mile of you, you can communicate with each other telepathically.</p>\n<p>You can't have more than one steed bonded by this spell at a time. As an action, you can release the steed from its bond at any time, causing it to disappear.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You summon a spirit that assumes the form of an unusually intelligent, strong, and loyal steed, creating a long-lasting bond with it. Appearing in an unoccupied space within range, the steed takes on a form that you choose: a warhorse, a pony, a camel, an elk, or a mastiff. (Your GM might allow other animals to be summoned as steeds.) The steed has the statistics of the chosen form, though it is a celestial, fey, or fiend (your choice) instead of its normal type. Additionally, if your steed has an Intelligence of 5 or less, its Intelligence becomes 6, and it gains the ability to understand one language of your choice that you speak.</p>\n<p>Your steed serves you as a mount, both in combat and out, and you have an instinctive bond with it that allows you to fight as a seamless unit. While mounted on your steed, you can make any spell you cast that targets only you also target your steed.</p>\n<p>When the steed drops to 0 hit points, it disappears, leaving behind no physical form. You can also dismiss your steed at any time as an action, causing it to disappear. In either case, casting this spell again summons the same steed, restored to its hit point maximum.</p>\n<p>While your steed is within 1 mile of you, you can communicate with each other telepathically.</p>\n<p>You can't have more than one steed bonded by this spell at a time. As an action, you can release the steed from its bond at any time, causing it to disappear.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 240","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.dkZ1IHTvqnK9pevg"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2098,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136804,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":240,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/wolf-paw-glow-teal-blue.webp","name":"Find Steed","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"VhHQHyj70P8qPffg","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. On each of your turns before the spell ends, you can use a bonus action to teleport in this way again.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. On each of your turns before the spell ends, you can use a bonus action to teleport in this way again.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 155","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.NBxGCfYxoFXXuqVH"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14870,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138096,"sources":[{"pageNumber":155,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Teleportation"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-black-pink.webp","name":"Far Step","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"VpieQNDVG5CHM7lb","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You summon elementals that appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. You choose one the following options for what appears:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One elemental of challenge rating 2 or lower</li>\n<li>Two elementals of challenge rating 1 or lower</li>\n<li>Four elementals of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</li>\n<li>Eight elementals of challenge rating 1/4 or lower.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />An elemental summoned by this spell disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p>\n<p>The GM has the creatures' statistics.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 6th-level slot and three times as many with an 8th-level slot.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Sample Elementals</strong></p>\n<table class=\"summoning-creatures-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>CR</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Monster</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1/4</td>\n<td>Steam Mephit</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1/2</td>\n<td>Dust Mephit, Ice Mephit, Magma Mephit, Magmin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Azer, Gargoyle</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You summon elementals that appear in unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. You choose one the following options for what appears:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One elemental of challenge rating 2 or lower</li>\n<li>Two elementals of challenge rating 1 or lower</li>\n<li>Four elementals of challenge rating 1/2 or lower</li>\n<li>Eight elementals of challenge rating 1/4 or lower.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />An elemental summoned by this spell disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.</p>\n<p>The GM has the creatures' statistics.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using certain higher-level spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more creatures appear: twice as many with a 6th-level slot and three times as many with an 8th-level slot.<br /><br /></p>\n<p><strong>Sample Elementals</strong></p>\n<table class=\"summoning-creatures-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>CR</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Monster</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1/4</td>\n<td>Steam Mephit</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1/2</td>\n<td>Dust Mephit, Ice Mephit, Magma Mephit, Magmin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Azer, Gargoyle</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":90},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 226","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.UDeI4Zg9FKCb7Tmz"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2043,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136282,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":226,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-orange.webp","name":"Conjure Minor Elementals","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"W6dUHFeknJGkrfOy","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":null,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":{"damage":"","threshold":null},"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","necrotic"],["@mod","healing"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"","unidentified":"","value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You invoke both death and life upon a 10-foot-radius sphere centered on a point within range. Each creature of your choice in that area must make a Constitution saving throw, taking [[/r 2d6]] necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Nonmagical vegetation in that area withers.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>In addition, one creature of your choice in that area can spend and roll one of its unspent Hit Dice and regain a number of hit points equal to the roll plus your spellcasting ability modifier.</p></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"7\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">At Higher Levels.</span></span> <p>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] for each slot above the 2nd, and the number of Hit Dice that can be spent and added to the healing roll increases by one for each slot above 2nd.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a withered vine twisted into a loop"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"SCC","target":{"type":"","units":"","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":"","1":""},"value":{"0":true,"1":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RM3M3YpjeqHVk1rN"},"srd5e":{"hash":"wither%20and%20bloom_scc","page":"spells.html","propDroppable":"spell","source":"SCC"}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/trap-spikes-thorns-green.webp","name":"Wither and Bloom","permission":{"OUGmAvuCIi3KewGn":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WBp7uSUQNIcJJ2Qj","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You become invisible at the same time that an illusory double of you appears where you are standing. The double lasts for the duration, but the invisibility ends if you attack or cast a spell.</p>\n<p>You can use your action to move your illusory double up to twice your speed and make it gesture, speak, and behave in whatever way you choose.</p>\n<p>You can see through its eyes and hear through its ears as if you were located where it is. On each of your turns as a bonus action, you can switch from using its senses to using your own, or back again. While you are using its senses, you are blinded and deafened in regard to your own surroundings.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You become invisible at the same time that an illusory double of you appears where you are standing. The double lasts for the duration, but the invisibility ends if you attack or cast a spell.</p>\n<p>You can use your action to move your illusory double up to twice your speed and make it gesture, speak, and behave in whatever way you choose.</p>\n<p>You can see through its eyes and hear through its ears as if you were located where it is. On each of your turns as a bonus action, you can switch from using its senses to using your own, or back again. While you are using its senses, you are blinded and deafened in regard to your own surroundings.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 260","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.gvRdDSQiUwBm0lP0"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2194,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138499,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":260,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Deception"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-energy-hold-levitate-blue-yellow.webp","name":"Mislead","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WWrFRErclQCr84Ju","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a pinch of sand","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You make a calming gesture, and up to three willing creatures of your choice that you can see within range fall unconscious for the spell’s duration. The spell ends on a target early if it takes damage or someone uses an action to shake or slap it awake. If a target remains unconscious for the full duration, that target gains the benefit of a short rest, and it can’t be affected by this spell again until it finishes a long rest.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional willing creature for each slot level above 3rd.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You make a calming gesture, and up to three willing creatures of your choice that you can see within range fall unconscious for the spell’s duration. The spell ends on a target early if it takes damage or someone uses an action to shake or slap it awake. If a target remains unconscious for the full duration, that target gains the benefit of a short rest, and it can’t be affected by this spell again until it finishes a long rest.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, you can target one additional willing creature for each slot level above 3rd.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a pinch of sand"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"enc","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 151","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":3,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.2xmRdlp09Gbw8n4t"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14754,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137941,"sources":[{"pageNumber":151,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff","Utility"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/perception/third-eye-blue-red.webp","name":"Catnap","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WZHp5e1E2obtOnwo","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a bit of fur from a bloodhound","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Describe or name a creature that is familiar to you. You sense the direction to the creature's location, as long as that creature is within 1,000 feet of you. If the creature is moving, you know the direction of its movement.</p>\n<p>The spell can locate a specific creature known to you, or the nearest creature of a specific kind (such as a human or a unicorn), so long as you have seen such a creature up close--within 30 feet--at least once. If the creature you described or named is in a different form, such as being under the effects of a <strong>polymorph</strong> spell, this spell doesn't locate the creature.</p>\n<p>This spell can't locate a creature if running water at least 10 feet wide blocks a direct path between you and the creature.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Describe or name a creature that is familiar to you. You sense the direction to the creature's location, as long as that creature is within 1,000 feet of you. If the creature is moving, you know the direction of its movement.</p>\n<p>The spell can locate a specific creature known to you, or the nearest creature of a specific kind (such as a human or a unicorn), so long as you have seen such a creature up close--within 30 feet--at least once. If the creature you described or named is in a different form, such as being under the effects of a <strong>polymorph</strong> spell, this spell doesn't locate the creature.</p>\n<p>This spell can't locate a creature if running water at least 10 feet wide blocks a direct path between you and the creature.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a bit of fur from a bloodhound"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 256","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.ZQtAA4F2seC8KeF8"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2169,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138411,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":256,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/leaf-glow-maple-orange-purple.webp","name":"Locate Creature","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WbrVBkw8eS9Esozm","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>For the duration, you sense the presence of magic within 30 feet of you. If you sense magic in this way, you can use your action to see a faint aura around any visible creature or object in the area that bears magic, and you learn its school of magic, if any.</p>\n<p>The spell can penetrate most barriers, but it is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood or dirt.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>For the duration, you sense the presence of magic within 30 feet of you. If you sense magic in this way, you can use your action to see a faint aura around any visible creature or object in the area that bears magic, and you learn its school of magic, if any.</p>\n<p>The spell can penetrate most barriers, but it is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood or dirt.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 231","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":30,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.Jj3v5jTvh1AMBLe7"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2065,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136561,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":231,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-blue.webp","name":"Detect Magic","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WeeKh8TxEdOrYrVi","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You awaken the sense of mortality in one creature you can see within range. A construct or an undead is immune to this effect. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become frightened of you until the spell ends. The frightened target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You awaken the sense of mortality in one creature you can see within range. A construct or an undead is immune to this effect. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become frightened of you until the spell ends. The frightened target can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 1st. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you target them.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 151","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.Fc3BXNMhwmhZGZCR"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14758,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137943,"sources":[{"pageNumber":151,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Debuff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/fear-fright-monster-green.webp","name":"Cause Fear","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WfCJLYHKm5M5gZw4","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","thunder"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>The first time you hit with a melee weapon attack during this spell’s duration, your weapon rings with thunder that is audible within 300 feet of you, and the attack deals an extra 2d6 thunder damage to the target. Additionally, if the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 10 feet away from you and knocked prone.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>The first time you hit with a melee weapon attack during this spell’s duration, your weapon rings with thunder that is audible within 300 feet of you, and the attack deals an extra 2d6 thunder damage to the target. Additionally, if the target is a creature, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed 10 feet away from you and knocked prone.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Player's Handbook pg 282","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.8FjGvZu5UgJaQ8E5"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2322,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138848,"sources":[{"pageNumber":282,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/fire/dagger-rune-enchant-flame-purple.webp","name":"Thunderous Smite","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WmF3Ujfsm4dla1Yy","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"rsak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"the stem of a plant with thorns","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":{"damage":"","threshold":null},"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes 1d6 piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.</p>\n<p>The spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes [[/r 1d6]] piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.</p>\n<p>The spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"the stem of a plant with thorns"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"cantrip"},"school":"trs","source":"Player's Handbook pg 282","target":{"type":"","units":"","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickAttack":{"value":true},"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.mEM3LtrR1vY28QR7"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2309,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138847,"sources":[{"pageNumber":282,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/root-vine-thorned-coil-green.webp","name":"Thorn Whip","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"WqLoDt0Oql386mAV","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"a small bit of honeycomb and jade dust worth at least 10 gp, which the spell consumes","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You implant a message within an object in range, a message that is uttered when a trigger condition is met. Choose an object that you can see and that isn't being worn or carried by another creature. Then speak the message, which must be 25 words or less, though it can be delivered over as long as 10 minutes. Finally, determine the circumstance that will trigger the spell to deliver your message.</p>\n<p>When that circumstance occurs, a magical mouth appears on the object and recites the message in your voice and at the same volume you spoke. If the object you chose has a mouth or something that looks like a mouth (for example, the mouth of a statue), the magical mouth appears there so that the words appear to come from the object's mouth. When you cast this spell, you can have the spell end after it delivers its message, or it can remain and repeat its message whenever the trigger occurs.</p>\n<p>The triggering circumstance can be as general or as detailed as you like, though it must be based on visual or audible conditions that occur within 30 feet of the object. For example, you could instruct the mouth to speak when any creature moves within 30 feet of the object or when a silver bell rings within 30 feet of it.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You implant a message within an object in range, a message that is uttered when a trigger condition is met. Choose an object that you can see and that isn't being worn or carried by another creature. Then speak the message, which must be 25 words or less, though it can be delivered over as long as 10 minutes. Finally, determine the circumstance that will trigger the spell to deliver your message.</p>\n<p>When that circumstance occurs, a magical mouth appears on the object and recites the message in your voice and at the same volume you spoke. If the object you chose has a mouth or something that looks like a mouth (for example, the mouth of a statue), the magical mouth appears there so that the words appear to come from the object's mouth. When you cast this spell, you can have the spell end after it delivers its message, or it can remain and repeat its message whenever the trigger occurs.</p>\n<p>The triggering circumstance can be as general or as detailed as you like, though it must be based on visual or audible conditions that occur within 30 feet of the object. For example, you could instruct the mouth to speak when any creature moves within 30 feet of the object or when a silver bell rings within 30 feet of it.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":10,"supply":0,"value":"a small bit of honeycomb and jade dust worth at least 10 gp, which the spell consumes"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 257","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.j2eR3yxz75V0AhCN"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2177,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138447,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":