{"_id":"Z7pvEfBKG6Wf3UG6","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"pieces of eggshell from two different kinds of creatures","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You forge a telepathic link among up to eight willing creatures of your choice within range, psychically linking each creature to all the others for the duration. Creatures with Intelligence scores of 2 or less aren't affected by this spell. </p>\n<p>Until the spell ends, the targets can communicate telepathically through the bond whether or not they have a common language. The communication is possible over any distance, though it can't extend to other planes of existence.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You forge a telepathic link among up to eight willing creatures of your choice within range, psychically linking each creature to all the others for the duration. Creatures with Intelligence scores of 2 or less aren't affected by this spell. </p>\n<p>Until the spell ends, the targets can communicate telepathically through the bond whether or not they have a common language. The communication is possible over any distance, though it can't extend to other planes of existence.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"pieces of eggshell from two different kinds of creatures"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":8,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.j8kX08CblJ6BcRAt"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2274,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":2423,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Communication"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/energy-stream-link-blue.webp","name":"Telepathic Bond","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"Z8ph1vbPjZJPTZXa","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a pinch of powdered iron or iron filings","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A 10-foot-radius invisible sphere of antimagic surrounds you. This area is divorced from the magical energy that suffuses the multiverse. Within the sphere, spells can't be cast, summoned creatures disappear, and even magic items become mundane. Until the spell ends, the sphere moves with you, centered on you.</p>\n<p>Spells and other magical effects, except those created by an artifact or a deity, are suppressed in the sphere and can't protrude into it. A slot expended to cast a suppressed spell is consumed. While an effect is suppressed, it doesn't function, but the time it spends suppressed counts against its duration.</p>\n<p><strong>Targeted Effects.</strong> Spells and other magical effects, such as <strong>magic missile</strong> and <strong>charm person</strong>, that target a creature or an object in the sphere have no effect on that target.</p>\n<p><strong>Areas of Magic.</strong> The area of another spell or magical effect, such as <strong>fireball</strong>, can't extend into the sphere. If the sphere overlaps an area of magic, the part of the area that is covered by the sphere is suppressed. For example, the flames created by a <strong>wall of fire</strong> are suppressed within the sphere, creating a gap in the wall if the overlap is large enough.</p>\n<p><strong>Spells.</strong> Any active spell or other magical effect on a creature or an object in the sphere is suppressed while the creature or object is in it.</p>\n<p><strong>Magic Items.</strong> The properties and powers of magic items are suppressed in the sphere. For example, a <strong>longsword, +1</strong> in the sphere functions as a nonmagical longsword.</p>\n<p>A magic weapon's properties and powers are suppressed if it is used against a target in the sphere or wielded by an attacker in the sphere. If a magic weapon or a piece of magic ammunition fully leaves the sphere (for example, if you fire a magic arrow or throw a magic spear at a target outside the sphere), the magic of the item ceases to be suppressed as soon as it exits.</p>\n<p><strong>Magical Travel.</strong> Teleportation and planar travel fail to work in the sphere, whether the sphere is the destination or the departure point for such magical travel. A portal to another location, world, or plane of existence, as well as an opening to an extradimensional space such as that created by the <strong>rope trick</strong> spell, temporarily closes while in the sphere.</p>\n<p><strong>Creatures and Objects.</strong> A creature or object summoned or created by magic temporarily winks out of existence in the sphere. Such a creature instantly reappears once the space the creature occupied is no longer within the sphere.</p>\n<p><strong>Dispel Magic.</strong> Spells and magical effects such as <strong>dispel magic</strong> have no effect on the sphere. Likewise, the spheres created by different <strong>antimagic field</strong> spells don't nullify each other.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A 10-foot-radius invisible sphere of antimagic surrounds you. This area is divorced from the magical energy that suffuses the multiverse. Within the sphere, spells can't be cast, summoned creatures disappear, and even magic items become mundane. Until the spell ends, the sphere moves with you, centered on you.</p>\n<p>Spells and other magical effects, except those created by an artifact or a deity, are suppressed in the sphere and can't protrude into it. A slot expended to cast a suppressed spell is consumed. While an effect is suppressed, it doesn't function, but the time it spends suppressed counts against its duration.</p>\n<p><strong>Targeted Effects.</strong> Spells and other magical effects, such as <strong>magic missile</strong> and <strong>charm person</strong>, that target a creature or an object in the sphere have no effect on that target.</p>\n<p><strong>Areas of Magic.</strong> The area of another spell or magical effect, such as <strong>fireball</strong>, can't extend into the sphere. If the sphere overlaps an area of magic, the part of the area that is covered by the sphere is suppressed. For example, the flames created by a <strong>wall of fire</strong> are suppressed within the sphere, creating a gap in the wall if the overlap is large enough.</p>\n<p><strong>Spells.</strong> Any active spell or other magical effect on a creature or an object in the sphere is suppressed while the creature or object is in it.</p>\n<p><strong>Magic Items.</strong> The properties and powers of magic items are suppressed in the sphere. For example, a <strong>longsword, +1</strong> in the sphere functions as a nonmagical longsword.</p>\n<p>A magic weapon's properties and powers are suppressed if it is used against a target in the sphere or wielded by an attacker in the sphere. If a magic weapon or a piece of magic ammunition fully leaves the sphere (for example, if you fire a magic arrow or throw a magic spear at a target outside the sphere), the magic of the item ceases to be suppressed as soon as it exits.</p>\n<p><strong>Magical Travel.</strong> Teleportation and planar travel fail to work in the sphere, whether the sphere is the destination or the departure point for such magical travel. A portal to another location, world, or plane of existence, as well as an opening to an extradimensional space such as that created by the <strong>rope trick</strong> spell, temporarily closes while in the sphere.</p>\n<p><strong>Creatures and Objects.</strong> A creature or object summoned or created by magic temporarily winks out of existence in the sphere. Such a creature instantly reappears once the space the creature occupied is no longer within the sphere.</p>\n<p><strong>Dispel Magic.</strong> Spells and magical effects such as <strong>dispel magic</strong> have no effect on the sphere. Likewise, the spheres created by different <strong>antimagic field</strong> spells don't nullify each other.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":8,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a pinch of powdered iron or iron filings"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"abj","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 213","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":10,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.LQI7YjgNBczZI1x6"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":1999,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136051,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":213,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Negation","Warding"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-chains-ropes-net-purple-blue.webp","name":"Antimagic Field","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZAJY7NeCdyRFyp4s","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"a piece of straw","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A whirlwind howls down to a point that you can see on the ground within range. The whirlwind is a 10-foot-radius, 30-foot-high cylinder centered on that point. Until the spell ends, you can use your action to move the whirlwind up to 30 feet in any direction along the ground. The whirlwind sucks up any Medium or smaller objects that aren’t secured to anything and that aren’t worn or carried by anyone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A creature must make a Dexterity saving throw the first time on a turn that it enters the whirlwind or that the whirlwind enters its space, including when the whirlwind first appears. A creature takes 10d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. In addition, a Large or smaller creature that fails the save must succeed on a Strength saving throw or become restrained in the whirlwind until the spell ends. When a creature starts its turn restrained by the whirlwind, the creature is pulled 5 feet higher inside it, unless the creature is at the top. A restrained creature moves with the whirlwind and falls when the spell ends, unless the creature has some means to stay aloft.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A restrained creature can use an action to make a Strength or Dexterity check against your spell save DC. If successful, the creature is no longer restrained by the whirlwind and is hurled 3d6 × 10 feet away from it in a random direction.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A whirlwind howls down to a point that you can see on the ground within range. The whirlwind is a 10-foot-radius, 30-foot-high cylinder centered on that point. Until the spell ends, you can use your action to move the whirlwind up to 30 feet in any direction along the ground. The whirlwind sucks up any Medium or smaller objects that aren’t secured to anything and that aren’t worn or carried by anyone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A creature must make a Dexterity saving throw the first time on a turn that it enters the whirlwind or that the whirlwind enters its space, including when the whirlwind first appears. A creature takes 10d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. In addition, a Large or smaller creature that fails the save must succeed on a Strength saving throw or become restrained in the whirlwind until the spell ends. When a creature starts its turn restrained by the whirlwind, the creature is pulled 5 feet higher inside it, unless the creature is at the top. A restrained creature moves with the whirlwind and falls when the spell ends, unless the creature has some means to stay aloft.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A restrained creature can use an action to make a Strength or Dexterity check against your spell save DC. If successful, the creature is no longer restrained by the whirlwind and is hurled 3d6 × 10 feet away from it in a random direction.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a piece of straw"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":300},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 171","target":{"type":"cylinder","units":"ft","value":10,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.bsbF1up17I1T3ME9"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2409,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138295,"sources":[{"pageNumber":171,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-cyclone-white.webp","name":"Whirlwind","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZJID8NcHu0Fpl3e6","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a miniature portal carved from ivory, a small piece of polished marble, and a tiny silver spoon, each item worth at least 5 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You conjure an extradimensional dwelling in range that lasts for the duration. You choose where its one entrance is located. The entrance shimmers faintly and is 5 feet wide and 10 feet tall. You and any creature you designate when you cast the spell can enter the extradimensional dwelling as long as the portal remains open. You can open or close the portal if you are within 30 feet of it. While closed, the portal is invisible.</p>\n<p>Beyond the portal is a magnificent foyer with numerous chambers beyond. The atmosphere is clean, fresh, and warm.</p>\n<p>You can create any floor plan you like, but the space can't exceed 50 cubes, each cube being 10 feet on each side. The place is furnished and decorated as you choose. It contains sufficient food to serve a nine-course banquet for up to 100 people. A staff of 100 near-transparent servants attends all who enter. You decide the visual appearance of these servants and their attire. They are completely obedient to your orders. Each servant can perform any task a normal human servant could perform, but they can't attack or take any action that would directly harm another creature. Thus the servants can fetch things, clean, mend, fold clothes, light fires, serve food, pour wine, and so on. The servants can go anywhere in the mansion but can't leave it. Furnishings and other objects created by this spell dissipate into smoke if removed from the mansion. When the spell ends, any creatures inside the extradimensional space are expelled into the open spaces nearest to the entrance.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You conjure an extradimensional dwelling in range that lasts for the duration. You choose where its one entrance is located. The entrance shimmers faintly and is 5 feet wide and 10 feet tall. You and any creature you designate when you cast the spell can enter the extradimensional dwelling as long as the portal remains open. You can open or close the portal if you are within 30 feet of it. While closed, the portal is invisible.</p>\n<p>Beyond the portal is a magnificent foyer with numerous chambers beyond. The atmosphere is clean, fresh, and warm.</p>\n<p>You can create any floor plan you like, but the space can't exceed 50 cubes, each cube being 10 feet on each side. The place is furnished and decorated as you choose. It contains sufficient food to serve a nine-course banquet for up to 100 people. A staff of 100 near-transparent servants attends all who enter. You decide the visual appearance of these servants and their attire. They are completely obedient to your orders. Each servant can perform any task a normal human servant could perform, but they can't attack or take any action that would directly harm another creature. Thus the servants can fetch things, clean, mend, fold clothes, light fires, serve food, pour wine, and so on. The servants can go anywhere in the mansion but can't leave it. Furnishings and other objects created by this spell dissipate into smoke if removed from the mansion. When the spell ends, any creatures inside the extradimensional space are expelled into the open spaces nearest to the entrance.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":24},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":5,"supply":0,"value":"a miniature portal carved from ivory, a small piece of polished marble, and a tiny silver spoon, each item worth at least 5 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":300},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.FnlwYbBGWDGI9pbq"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2179,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":2451,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Utility","Exploration"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange-purple.webp","name":"Magnificent Mansion","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZZHAsSPPMsIRkL1O","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","piercing"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>The next time you hit a creature with a weapon attack before this spell ends, a writhing mass of thorny vines appears at the point of impact, and the target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be restrained by the magical vines until the spell ends. A Large or larger creature has advantage on this saving throw. If the target succeeds on the save, the vines shrivel away. <br /><br />While restrained by this spell, the target takes 1d6 piercing damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature restrained by the vines or one that can touch the creature can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target is freed. </p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels. </strong>If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>The next time you hit a creature with a weapon attack before this spell ends, a writhing mass of thorny vines appears at the point of impact, and the target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be restrained by the magical vines until the spell ends. A Large or larger creature has advantage on this saving throw. If the target succeeds on the save, the vines shrivel away. <br /><br />While restrained by this spell, the target takes 1d6 piercing damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature restrained by the vines or one that can touch the creature can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target is freed. </p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels. </strong>If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"level"},"school":"con","source":"Player's Handbook pg 237","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.6BySf4GoP4Mpe4v3"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2315,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136715,"sources":[{"pageNumber":237,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/fire/projectile-arrow-fire-red-yellow.webp","name":"Ensnaring Strike","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZccZMdifzoXKmSRX","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"msak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":"","chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":{"damage":"","threshold":null},"damage":{"parts":[["1d8","fire"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A flickering flame appears in your hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.</p>\n<p>You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 fire damage.</p>\n<p>This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A flickering flame appears in your hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.</p>\n<p>You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes [[/r 1d8]] fire damage.</p>\n<p>This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d8","mode":"cantrip"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 269","target":{"type":"creature","units":"","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickAttack":{"value":true},"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.iauqLdhseX8cKSdH"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2217,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138596,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":269,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Creation","Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/fire/explosion-fireball-medium-orange.webp","name":"Produce Flame","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZhB6salYdtBDkUho","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a small parchment with a bit of holy text written on it","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A shimmering field appears and surrounds a creature of your choice within range, granting it a +2 bonus to AC for the duration.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A shimmering field appears and surrounds a creature of your choice within range, granting it a +2 bonus to AC for the duration.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a small parchment with a bit of holy text written on it"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"abj","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 275","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.zmaElfAwTxhMN2s2"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2248,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138705,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":275,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Buff","Warding"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-diamond-blue-yellow.webp","name":"Shield of Faith","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZrvUvdNUZlpB4SG5","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a bit of sponge","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["12d8","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You draw the moisture from every creature in a 30-foot cube centered on a point you choose within range. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. Constructs and undead aren’t affected, and plants and water elementals make this saving throw with disadvantage. A creature takes 12d8 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Nonmagical plants in the area that aren’t creatures, such as trees and shrubs, wither and die instantly.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You draw the moisture from every creature in a 30-foot cube centered on a point you choose within range. Each creature in that area must make a Constitution saving throw. Constructs and undead aren’t affected, and plants and water elementals make this saving throw with disadvantage. A creature takes 12d8 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Nonmagical plants in the area that aren’t creatures, such as trees and shrubs, wither and die instantly.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":8,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a bit of sponge"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":150},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 150","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":30,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"0","per":"","value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.M6hnEV5HvdxnBwEA"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2367,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137855,"sources":[{"pageNumber":150,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-dense-brown.webp","name":"Abi-Dalzim's Horrid Wilting","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ZvIJ0sRq5o2Lj29y","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a drop of water and a pinch of dust","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d8","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Until the spell ends, you control any freestanding water inside an area you choose that is a cube up to 100 feet on a side. You can choose from any of the following effects when you cast this spell. As an action on your turn, you can repeat the same effect or choose a different one.</p>\n<p><strong>Flood.</strong> You cause the water level of all standing water in the area to rise by as much as 20 feet. If the area includes a shore, the flooding water spills over onto dry land.</p>\n<p>If you choose an area in a large body of water, you instead create a 20-foot tall wave that travels from one side of the area to the other and then crashes down. Any Huge or smaller vehicles in the wave's path are carried with it to the other side. Any Huge or smaller vehicles struck by the wave have a 25 percent chance of capsizing.</p>\n<p>The water level remains elevated until the spell ends or you choose a different effect. If this effect produced a wave, the wave repeats on the start of your next turn while the flood effect lasts.</p>\n<p><strong>Part Water.</strong> You cause water in the area to move apart and create a trench. The trench extends across the spell's area, and the separated water forms a wall to either side. The trench remains until the spell ends or you choose a different effect. The water then slowly fills in the trench over the course of the next round until the normal water level is restored.</p>\n<p><strong>Redirect Flow.</strong> You cause flowing water in the area to move in a direction you choose, even if the water has to flow over obstacles, up walls, or in other unlikely directions. The water in the area moves as you direct it, but once it moves beyond the spell's area, it resumes its flow based on the terrain conditions. The water continues to move in the direction you chose until the spell ends or you choose a different effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Whirlpool.</strong> This effect requires a body of water at least 50 feet square and 25 feet deep. You cause a whirlpool to form in the center of the area. The whirlpool forms a vortex that is 5 feet wide at the base, up to 50 feet wide at the top, and 25 feet tall. Any creature or object in the water and within 25 feet of the vortex is pulled 10 feet toward it. A creature can swim away from the vortex by making a Strength (Athletics) check against your spell save DC.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the vortex for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 2d8 bludgeoning damage and is caught in the vortex until the spell ends. On a successful save, the creature takes half damage, and isn't caught in the vortex. A creature caught in the vortex can use its action to try to swim away from the vortex as described above, but has disadvantage on the Strength (Athletics) check to do so.</p>\n<p>The first time each turn that an object enters the vortex, the object takes 2d8 bludgeoning damage; this damage occurs each round it remains in the vortex.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Until the spell ends, you control any freestanding water inside an area you choose that is a cube up to 100 feet on a side. You can choose from any of the following effects when you cast this spell. As an action on your turn, you can repeat the same effect or choose a different one.</p>\n<p><strong>Flood.</strong> You cause the water level of all standing water in the area to rise by as much as 20 feet. If the area includes a shore, the flooding water spills over onto dry land.</p>\n<p>If you choose an area in a large body of water, you instead create a 20-foot tall wave that travels from one side of the area to the other and then crashes down. Any Huge or smaller vehicles in the wave's path are carried with it to the other side. Any Huge or smaller vehicles struck by the wave have a 25 percent chance of capsizing.</p>\n<p>The water level remains elevated until the spell ends or you choose a different effect. If this effect produced a wave, the wave repeats on the start of your next turn while the flood effect lasts.</p>\n<p><strong>Part Water.</strong> You cause water in the area to move apart and create a trench. The trench extends across the spell's area, and the separated water forms a wall to either side. The trench remains until the spell ends or you choose a different effect. The water then slowly fills in the trench over the course of the next round until the normal water level is restored.</p>\n<p><strong>Redirect Flow.</strong> You cause flowing water in the area to move in a direction you choose, even if the water has to flow over obstacles, up walls, or in other unlikely directions. The water in the area moves as you direct it, but once it moves beyond the spell's area, it resumes its flow based on the terrain conditions. The water continues to move in the direction you chose until the spell ends or you choose a different effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Whirlpool.</strong> This effect requires a body of water at least 50 feet square and 25 feet deep. You cause a whirlpool to form in the center of the area. The whirlpool forms a vortex that is 5 feet wide at the base, up to 50 feet wide at the top, and 25 feet tall. Any creature or object in the water and within 25 feet of the vortex is pulled 10 feet toward it. A creature can swim away from the vortex by making a Strength (Athletics) check against your spell save DC.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the vortex for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 2d8 bludgeoning damage and is caught in the vortex until the spell ends. On a successful save, the creature takes half damage, and isn't caught in the vortex. A creature caught in the vortex can use its action to try to swim away from the vortex as described above, but has disadvantage on the Strength (Athletics) check to do so.</p>\n<p>The first time each turn that an object enters the vortex, the object takes 2d8 bludgeoning damage; this damage occurs each round it remains in the vortex.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a drop of water and a pinch of dust"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":300},"save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 227","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.ZDZjeW9RzEKFaZPl"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2049,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136433,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":227,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-swirling-blue.webp","name":"Control Water","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aDcarnAJLjfpsV6h","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["10d6","fire"],["10d6","acid"],["10d6","lightning"],["10d6","poison"],["10d6","cold"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Eight multicolored rays of light flash from your hand. Each ray is a different color and has a different power and purpose. Each creature in a 60-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. For each target, roll a d8 to determine which color ray affects it.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Red.</strong> The target takes 10d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Orange.</strong> The target takes 10d6 acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Yellow.</strong> The target takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Green.</strong> The target takes 10d6 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Blue.</strong> The target takes 10d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>6. Indigo.</strong> On a failed save, the target is restrained. It must then make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If it successfully saves three times, the spell ends. If it fails its save three times, it permanently turns to stone and is subjected to the petrified condition. The successes and failures don't need to be consecutive; keep track of both until the target collects three of a kind.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Violet.</strong> On a failed save, the target is blinded. It must then make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of your next turn. A successful save ends the blindness. If it fails that save, the creature is transported to another plane of existence of the GM's choosing and is no longer blinded. (Typically, a creature that is on a plane that isn't its home plane is banished home, while other creatures are usually cast into the Astral or Ethereal planes.) </p>\n<p><strong>8. Special.</strong> The target is struck by two rays. Roll twice more, rerolling any 8.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Eight multicolored rays of light flash from your hand. Each ray is a different color and has a different power and purpose. Each creature in a 60-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. For each target, roll a d8 to determine which color ray affects it.</p>\n<p><strong>1. Red.</strong> The target takes 10d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>2. Orange.</strong> The target takes 10d6 acid damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>3. Yellow.</strong> The target takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>4. Green.</strong> The target takes 10d6 poison damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>5. Blue.</strong> The target takes 10d6 cold damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p><strong>6. Indigo.</strong> On a failed save, the target is restrained. It must then make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. If it successfully saves three times, the spell ends. If it fails its save three times, it permanently turns to stone and is subjected to the petrified condition. The successes and failures don't need to be consecutive; keep track of both until the target collects three of a kind.</p>\n<p><strong>7. Violet.</strong> On a failed save, the target is blinded. It must then make a Wisdom saving throw at the start of your next turn. A successful save ends the blindness. If it fails that save, the creature is transported to another plane of existence of the GM's choosing and is no longer blinded. (Typically, a creature that is on a plane that isn't its home plane is banished home, while other creatures are usually cast into the Astral or Ethereal planes.) </p>\n<p><strong>8. Special.</strong> The target is struck by two rays. Roll twice more, rerolling any 8.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 267","target":{"type":"cone","units":"ft","value":60,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.E17QHFpaZ1CnxfSJ"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2214,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138593,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":267,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-beams-salvo-yellow.webp","name":"Prismatic Spray","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aF5gxqksxSRSAA9c","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["14d6","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You unleash a virulent disease on a creature that you can see within range. The target must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 14d6 necrotic damage, or half as much damage on a successful save. The damage can't reduce the target's hit points below 1. If the target fails the saving throw, its hit point maximum is reduced for 1 hour by an amount equal to the necrotic damage it took. Any effect that removes a disease allows a creature's hit point maximum to return to normal before that time passes.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You unleash a virulent disease on a creature that you can see within range. The target must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 14d6 necrotic damage, or half as much damage on a successful save. The damage can't reduce the target's hit points below 1. If the target fails the saving throw, its hit point maximum is reduced for 1 hour by an amount equal to the necrotic damage it took. Any effect that removes a disease allows a creature's hit point maximum to return to normal before that time passes.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 249","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.OMBmdwautrWQOsxv"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2137,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138037,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":249,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Debuff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-beam-blood-large-red-purple.webp","name":"Harm","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aJuu3LSLKh4b6lCQ","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d8","psychic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You reach into the mind of one creature you can see within range. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, taking 3d8 psychic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. On a failed save, you also always know the target’s location until the spell ends, but only while the two of you are on the same plane of existence. While you have this knowledge, the target can’t become hidden from you, and if it’s invisible, it gains no benefit from that condition against you.</p>\n<p><strong><em>At Higher Levels.</em> </strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 2nd.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You reach into the mind of one creature you can see within range. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, taking 3d8 psychic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. On a failed save, you also always know the target’s location until the spell ends, but only while the two of you are on the same plane of existence. While you have this knowledge, the target can’t become hidden from you, and if it’s invisible, it gains no benefit from that condition against you.</p>\n<p><strong><em>At Higher Levels.</em> </strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 2nd.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d8","mode":"level"},"school":"div","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 162","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.qaPx1vUoMMtS3bfp"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14482,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":147146,"sources":[{"pageNumber":162,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/weapons/guns/arrowhead-glowing-blue.webp","name":"Mind Spike","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aUKsrHPbwR9O7kLo","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"heal","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","healing"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You call forth a nature spirit to soothe the wounded. The intangible spirit appears in a space that is a 5-foot cube you can see within range. The spirit looks like a transparent beast or fey (your choice).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Until the spell ends, whenever you or a creature you can see moves into the spirit’s space for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, you can cause the spirit to restore 1d6 hit points to that creature (no action required). The spirit can’t heal constructs or undead. The spirit can heal a number of times equal to 1 + your spellcasting ability modifier (minimum of twice). After healing that number of times, the spirit disappears.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the spirit up to 30 feet to a space you can see.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the healing increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 2nd.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You call forth a nature spirit to soothe the wounded. The intangible spirit appears in a space that is a 5-foot cube you can see within range. The spirit looks like a transparent beast or fey (your choice).</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Until the spell ends, whenever you or a creature you can see moves into the spirit’s space for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, you can cause the spirit to restore 1d6 hit points to that creature (no action required). The spirit can’t heal constructs or undead. The spirit can heal a number of times equal to 1 + your spellcasting ability modifier (minimum of twice). After healing that number of times, the spirit disappears.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the spirit up to 30 feet to a space you can see.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the healing increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 2nd.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"level"},"school":"con","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 157","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":5,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.Tsie1QDXbrI4B6e2"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14873,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138113,"sources":[{"pageNumber":157,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Healing","Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/beam-rays-yellow-blue-small.webp","name":"Healing Spirit","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aYBH3a3Haob931b2","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":10,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"a sprinkling of holy water, rare incense, and powdered ruby worth at least 1,000 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d10","radiant"],["5d10","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create a ward against magical travel that protects up to 40,000 square feet of floor space to a height of 30 feet above the floor. For the duration, creatures can't teleport into the area or use portals, such as those created by the <strong>gate</strong> spell, to enter the area. The spell proofs the area against planar travel, and therefore prevents creatures from accessing the area by way of the Astral Plane, Ethereal Plane, Feywild, Shadowfell, or the <strong>plane shift</strong> spell.</p>\n<p>In addition, the spell damages types of creatures that you choose when you cast it. Choose one or more of the following: celestials, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead. When a chosen creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature takes 5d10 radiant or necrotic damage (your choice when you cast this spell).</p>\n<p>When you cast this spell, you can designate a password. A creature that speaks the password as it enters the area takes no damage from the spell.</p>\n<p>The spell's area can't overlap with the area of another <strong>forbiddance</strong> spell. If you cast <strong>forbiddance</strong> every day for 30 days in the same location, the spell lasts until it is dispelled, and the material components are consumed on the last casting.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create a ward against magical travel that protects up to 40,000 square feet of floor space to a height of 30 feet above the floor. For the duration, creatures can't teleport into the area or use portals, such as those created by the <strong>gate</strong> spell, to enter the area. The spell proofs the area against planar travel, and therefore prevents creatures from accessing the area by way of the Astral Plane, Ethereal Plane, Feywild, Shadowfell, or the <strong>plane shift</strong> spell.</p>\n<p>In addition, the spell damages types of creatures that you choose when you cast it. Choose one or more of the following: celestials, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead. When a chosen creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature takes 5d10 radiant or necrotic damage (your choice when you cast this spell).</p>\n<p>When you cast this spell, you can designate a password. A creature that speaks the password as it enters the area takes no damage from the spell.</p>\n<p>The spell's area can't overlap with the area of another <strong>forbiddance</strong> spell. If you cast <strong>forbiddance</strong> every day for 30 days in the same location, the spell lasts until it is dispelled, and the material components are consumed on the last casting.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"day","value":1},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":1000,"supply":0,"value":"a sprinkling of holy water, rare incense, and powdered ruby worth at least 1,000 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"abj","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 243","target":{"type":"square feet","units":"ft","value":40000,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.ILQW4Dln21WT9lco"},"d