{"_id":"agKrZytCJhBhDSv9","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":24,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"herbs, oils, and incense worth at least 1,000 gp, which the spell consumes","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You touch a point and infuse an area around it with holy (or unholy) power. The area can have a radius up to 60 feet, and the spell fails if the radius includes an area already under the effect a <strong>hallow</strong> spell. The affected area is subject to the following effects.</p>\n<p>First, celestials, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead can't enter the area, nor can such creatures charm, frighten, or possess creatures within it. Any creature charmed, frightened, or possessed by such a creature is no longer charmed, frightened, or possessed upon entering the area. You can exclude one or more of those types of creatures from this effect.</p>\n<p>Second, you can bind an extra effect to the area. Choose the effect from the following list, or choose an effect offered by the GM. Some of these effects apply to creatures in the area; you can designate whether the effect applies to all creatures, creatures that follow a specific deity or leader, or creatures of a specific sort, such as orcs or trolls. When a creature that would be affected enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it can make a Charisma saving throw. On a success, the creature ignores the extra effect until it leaves the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Courage.</strong> Affected creatures can't be frightened while in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Darkness.</strong> Darkness fills the area. Normal light, as well as magical light created by spells of a lower level than the slot you used to cast this spell, can't illuminate the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Daylight.</strong> Bright light fills the area. Magical darkness created by spells of a lower level than the slot you used to cast this spell can't extinguish the light.</p>\n<p><strong>Energy Protection.</strong> Affected creatures in the area have resistance to one damage type of your choice, except for bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing.</p>\n<p><strong>Energy Vulnerability.</strong> Affected creatures in the area have vulnerability to one damage type of your choice, except for bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing.</p>\n<p><strong>Everlasting Rest.</strong> Dead bodies interred in the area can't be turned into undead.</p>\n<p><strong>Extradimensional Interference.</strong> Affected creatures can't move or travel using teleportation or by extradimensional or interplanar means.</p>\n<p><strong>Fear.</strong> Affected creatures are frightened while in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Silence.</strong> No sound can emanate from within the area, and no sound can reach into it.</p>\n<p><strong>Tongues.</strong> Affected creatures can communicate with any other creature in the area, even if they don't share a common language.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You touch a point and infuse an area around it with holy (or unholy) power. The area can have a radius up to 60 feet, and the spell fails if the radius includes an area already under the effect a <strong>hallow</strong> spell. The affected area is subject to the following effects.</p>\n<p>First, celestials, elementals, fey, fiends, and undead can't enter the area, nor can such creatures charm, frighten, or possess creatures within it. Any creature charmed, frightened, or possessed by such a creature is no longer charmed, frightened, or possessed upon entering the area. You can exclude one or more of those types of creatures from this effect.</p>\n<p>Second, you can bind an extra effect to the area. Choose the effect from the following list, or choose an effect offered by the GM. Some of these effects apply to creatures in the area; you can designate whether the effect applies to all creatures, creatures that follow a specific deity or leader, or creatures of a specific sort, such as orcs or trolls. When a creature that would be affected enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it can make a Charisma saving throw. On a success, the creature ignores the extra effect until it leaves the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Courage.</strong> Affected creatures can't be frightened while in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Darkness.</strong> Darkness fills the area. Normal light, as well as magical light created by spells of a lower level than the slot you used to cast this spell, can't illuminate the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Daylight.</strong> Bright light fills the area. Magical darkness created by spells of a lower level than the slot you used to cast this spell can't extinguish the light.</p>\n<p><strong>Energy Protection.</strong> Affected creatures in the area have resistance to one damage type of your choice, except for bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing.</p>\n<p><strong>Energy Vulnerability.</strong> Affected creatures in the area have vulnerability to one damage type of your choice, except for bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing.</p>\n<p><strong>Everlasting Rest.</strong> Dead bodies interred in the area can't be turned into undead.</p>\n<p><strong>Extradimensional Interference.</strong> Affected creatures can't move or travel using teleportation or by extradimensional or interplanar means.</p>\n<p><strong>Fear.</strong> Affected creatures are frightened while in the area.</p>\n<p><strong>Silence.</strong> No sound can emanate from within the area, and no sound can reach into it.</p>\n<p><strong>Tongues.</strong> Affected creatures can communicate with any other creature in the area, even if they don't share a common language.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":1000,"supply":0,"value":"herbs, oils, and incense worth at least 1,000 gp, which the spell consumes"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 249","target":{"type":"sphere","units":"ft","value":60,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.im8gMI8P5AAg5q5Y"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2135,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138030,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":249,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Buff","Debuff","Environment"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-large-teal.webp","name":"Hallow","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"aiQbXRSJyLgQlofD","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"a broken bone and a square of black silk","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["5d12","necrotic"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You send ribbons of negative energy at one creature you can see within range. Unless the target is undead, it must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 5d12 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A target killed by this damage rises up as a zombie at the start of your next turn. The zombie pursues whatever creature it can see that is closest to it. Statistics for the zombie are in the <a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/mm/monsters-z#Zombies\"><em><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">Monst</span><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">er Manual</span></em></a>.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">If you target an undead with this spell, the target doesn’t make a saving throw. Instead, roll 5d12. The target gains half the total as temporary hit points.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You send ribbons of negative energy at one creature you can see within range. Unless the target is undead, it must make a Constitution saving throw, taking 5d12 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A target killed by this damage rises up as a zombie at the start of your next turn. The zombie pursues whatever creature it can see that is closest to it. Statistics for the zombie are in the <a href=\"https://www.dndbeyond.com/compendium/rules/mm/monsters-z#Zombies\"><em><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">Monst</span><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">er Manual</span></em></a>.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">If you target an undead with this spell, the target doesn’t make a saving throw. Instead, roll 5d12. The target gains half the total as temporary hit points.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a broken bone and a square of black silk"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 163","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.dOPOtllqLosGbsye"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14519,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138208,"sources":[{"pageNumber":163,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Creation","Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/unholy/strike-beam-blood-large-red-green.webp","name":"Negative Energy Flood","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"atXzl9cQOCBYDZAN","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"a pinch of salt and one copper piece placed on each of the corpse's eyes, which must remain there for the duration","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You touch a corpse or other remains. For the duration, the target is protected from decay and can't become undead.</p>\n<p>The spell also effectively extends the time limit on raising the target from the dead, since days spent under the influence of this spell don't count against the time limit of spells such as <strong>raise dead</strong>.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You touch a corpse or other remains. For the duration, the target is protected from decay and can't become undead.</p>\n<p>The spell also effectively extends the time limit on raising the target from the dead, since days spent under the influence of this spell don't count against the time limit of spells such as <strong>raise dead</strong>.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"day","value":10},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a pinch of salt and one copper piece placed on each of the corpse's eyes, which must remain there for the duration"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 245","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"c