{"_id":"eVLna3D0AEHn4ihf","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","fire"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>As you hold your hands with thumbs touching and fingers spread, a thin sheet of flames shoots forth from your outstretched fingertips. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 3d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The fire ignites any flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>As you hold your hands with thumbs touching and fingers spread, a thin sheet of flames shoots forth from your outstretched fingertips. Each creature in a 15-foot cone must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 3d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>The fire ignites any flammable objects in the area that aren't being worn or carried.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"level"},"school":"evo","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 220","target":{"type":"cone","units":"ft","value":15,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.h9imuXbHMjq4pkWa"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2021,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136168,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":220,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-dense-orange.webp","name":"Burning Hands","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"eYlZOT4sZ5KSYM8G","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a gem, crystal, reliquary, or some other ornamental container worth at least 500 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Your body falls into a catatonic state as your soul leaves it and enters the container you used for the spell's material component. While your soul inhabits the container, you are aware of your surroundings as if you were in the container's space. You can't move or use reactions. The only action you can take is to project your soul up to 100 feet out of the container, either returning to your living body (and ending the spell) or attempting to possess a humanoids body.</p>\n<p>You can attempt to possess any humanoid within 100 feet of you that you can see (creatures warded by a <strong>protection from evil and good</strong> or <strong>magic circle</strong> spell can't be possessed). The target must make a Charisma saving throw. On a failure, your soul moves into the target's body, and the target's soul becomes trapped in the container. On a success, the target resists your efforts to possess it, and you can't attempt to possess it again for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Once you possess a creature's body, you control it. Your game statistics are replaced by the statistics of the creature, though you retain your alignment and your Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores. You retain the benefit of your own class features. If the target has any class levels, you can't use any of its class features.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, the possessed creature's soul can perceive from the container using its own senses, but it can't move or take actions at all.</p>\n<p>While possessing a body, you can use your action to return from the host body to the container if it is within 100 feet of you, returning the host creature's soul to its body. If the host body dies while you're in it, the creature dies, and you must make a Charisma saving throw against your own spellcasting DC. On a success, you return to the container if it is within 100 feet of you. Otherwise, you die.</p>\n<p>If the container is destroyed or the spell ends, your soul immediately returns to your body. If your body is more than 100 feet away from you or if your body is dead when you attempt to return to it, you die. If another creature's soul is in the container when it is destroyed, the creature's soul returns to its body if the body is alive and within 100 feet. Otherwise, that creature dies.</p>\n<p>When the spell ends, the container is destroyed.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Your body falls into a catatonic state as your soul leaves it and enters the container you used for the spell's material component. While your soul inhabits the container, you are aware of your surroundings as if you were in the container's space. You can't move or use reactions. The only action you can take is to project your soul up to 100 feet out of the container, either returning to your living body (and ending the spell) or attempting to possess a humanoids body.</p>\n<p>You can attempt to possess any humanoid within 100 feet of you that you can see (creatures warded by a <strong>protection from evil and good</strong> or <strong>magic circle</strong> spell can't be possessed). The target must make a Charisma saving throw. On a failure, your soul moves into the target's body, and the target's soul becomes trapped in the container. On a success, the target resists your efforts to possess it, and you can't attempt to possess it again for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>Once you possess a creature's body, you control it. Your game statistics are replaced by the statistics of the creature, though you retain your alignment and your Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores. You retain the benefit of your own class features. If the target has any class levels, you can't use any of its class features.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, the possessed creature's soul can perceive from the container using its own senses, but it can't move or take actions at all.</p>\n<p>While possessing a body, you can use your action to return from the host body to the container if it is within 100 feet of you, returning the host creature's soul to its body. If the host body dies while you're in it, the creature dies, and you must make a Charisma saving throw against your own spellcasting DC. On a success, you return to the container if it is within 100 feet of you. Otherwise, you die.</p>\n<p>If the container is destroyed or the spell ends, your soul immediately returns to your body. If your body is more than 100 feet away from you or if your body is dead when you attempt to return to it, you die. If another creature's soul is in the container when it is destroyed, the creature's soul returns to its body if the body is alive and within 100 feet. Otherwise, that creature dies.</p>\n<p>When the spell ends, the container is destroyed.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":500,"supply":0,"value":"a gem, crystal, reliquary, or some other ornamental container worth at least 500 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 257","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.p0H3nOrqcvBeRyHX"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2175,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138442,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":257,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-pentagon-teal-purple.webp","name":"Magic Jar","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ecwXzAtcLuJYTvNC","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"rsak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["4d12","force"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create a blade-shaped planar rift about 3 feet long in an unoccupied space you can see within range. The blade lasts for the duration. When you cast this spell, you can make up to two melee spell attacks with the blade, each one against a creature, loose object, or structure within 5 feet of the blade. On a hit, the target takes 4d12 force damage. This attack scores a critical hit if the number on the d20 is 18 or higher. On a critical hit, the blade deals an extra 8d12 force damage (for a total of 12d12 force damage).</p>\n<p>As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the blade up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see and then make up to two melee spell attacks with it again.</p>\n<p>The blade can harmlessly pass through any barrier, including a wall of force.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create a blade-shaped planar rift about 3 feet long in an unoccupied space you can see within range. The blade lasts for the duration. When you cast this spell, you can make up to two melee spell attacks with the blade, each one against a creature, loose object, or structure within 5 feet of the blade. On a hit, the target takes 4d12 force damage. This attack scores a critical hit if the number on the d20 is 18 or higher. On a critical hit, the blade deals an extra 8d12 force damage (for a total of 12d12 force damage).</p>\n<p>As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the blade up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see and then make up to two melee spell attacks with it again.</p>\n<p>The blade can harmlessly pass through any barrier, including a wall of force.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":9,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Icewind Dale: Rime of the Frostmaiden pg 318","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.JMsSMWArwAOzO44Q"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":654072,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":5963077,"sources":[{"pageNumber":318,"sourceId":66,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-sword-blood-red.webp","name":"Blade of Disaster","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"en1JLo32E4izIekz","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"heal","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a diamond worth at least 500 gp, which the spell consumes","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You return a dead creature you touch to life, provided that it has been dead no longer than 10 days. If the creature's soul is both willing and at liberty to rejoin the body, the creature returns to life with 1 hit point.</p>\n<p>This spell also neutralizes any poisons and cures nonmagical diseases that affected the creature at the time it died. This spell doesn't, however, remove magical diseases, curses, or similar effects; if these aren't first removed prior to casting the spell, they take effect when the creature returns to life. The spell can't return an undead creature to life.</p>\n<p>This spell closes all mortal wounds, but it doesn't restore missing body parts. If the creature is lacking body parts or organs integral for its survival--its head, for instance--the spell automatically fails.</p>\n<p>Coming back from the dead is an ordeal. The target takes a −4 penalty to all attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks. Every time the target finishes a long rest, the penalty is reduced by 1 until it disappears.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You return a dead creature you touch to life, provided that it has been dead no longer than 10 days. If the creature's soul is both willing and at liberty to rejoin the body, the creature returns to life with 1 hit point.</p>\n<p>This spell also neutralizes any poisons and cures nonmagical diseases that affected the creature at the time it died. This spell doesn't, however, remove magical diseases, curses, or similar effects; if these aren't first removed prior to casting the spell, they take effect when the creature returns to life. The spell can't return an undead creature to life.</p>\n<p>This spell closes all mortal wounds, but it doesn't restore missing body parts. If the creature is lacking body parts or organs integral for its survival--its head, for instance--the spell automatically fails.</p>\n<p>Coming back from the dead is an ordeal. The target takes a −4 penalty to all attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks. Every time the target finishes a long rest, the penalty is reduced by 1 until it disappears.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":500,"supply":0,"value":"a diamond worth at least 500 gp, which the spell consumes"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 270","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.9H92P9YpeCZ2uxNZ"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2224,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138623,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":270,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Healing"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/life/heart-cross-strong-purple-orange.webp","name":"Raise Dead","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"enlynm8CxTEO2jxj","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":12,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"snow or ice in quantities sufficient to make a life-size copy of the duplicated creature; some hair, fingernail clippings, or other piece of that creature's body placed inside the snow or ice; and powdered ruby worth 1,500 gp, sprinkled over the duplicate and consumed by the spell","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You shape an illusory duplicate of one beast or humanoid that is within range for the entire casting time of the spell. The duplicate is a creature, partially real and formed from ice or snow, and it can take actions and otherwise be affected as a normal creature. It appears to be the same as the original, but it has half the creature's hit point maximum and is formed without any equipment. Otherwise, the illusion uses all the statistics of the creature it duplicates, except that it is a construct.</p>\n<p>The simulacrum is friendly to you and creatures you designate. It obeys your spoken commands, moving and acting in accordance with your wishes and acting on your turn in combat. The simulacrum lacks the ability to learn or become more powerful, so it never increases its level or other abilities, nor can it regain expended spell slots.</p>\n<p>If the simulacrum is damaged, you can repair it in an alchemical laboratory, using rare herbs and minerals worth 100 gp per hit point it regains. The simulacrum lasts until it drops to 0 hit points, at which point it reverts to snow and melts instantly.</p>\n<p>If you cast this spell again, any duplicate you created with this spell is instantly destroyed.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You shape an illusory duplicate of one beast or humanoid that is within range for the entire casting time of the spell. The duplicate is a creature, partially real and formed from ice or snow, and it can take actions and otherwise be affected as a normal creature. It appears to be the same as the original, but it has half the creature's hit point maximum and is formed without any equipment. Otherwise, the illusion uses all the statistics of the creature it duplicates, except that it is a construct.</p>\n<p>The simulacrum is friendly to you and creatures you designate. It obeys your spoken commands, moving and acting in accordance with your wishes and acting on your turn in combat. The simulacrum lacks the ability to learn or become more powerful, so it never increases its level or other abilities, nor can it regain expended spell slots.</p>\n<p>If the simulacrum is damaged, you can repair it in an alchemical laboratory, using rare herbs and minerals worth 100 gp per hit point it regains. The simulacrum lasts until it drops to 0 hit points, at which point it reverts to snow and melts instantly.</p>\n<p>If you cast this spell again, any duplicate you created with this spell is instantly destroyed.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":1500,"supply":0,"value":"snow or ice in quantities sufficient to make a life-size copy of the duplicated creature; some hair, fingernail clippings, or other piece of that creature's body placed inside the snow or ice; and powdered ruby worth 1,500 gp, sprinkled over the duplicate and consumed by the spell"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 276","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.TN8caueZ09Dv53YY"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2253,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138721,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":276,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Utility","Deception"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/energy-stream-link-spiral-orange.webp","name":"Simulacrum","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ersoOQnJs7n6PrH6","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You choose an area of water that you can see within range and that fits within a 5-foot cube. You manipulate it in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously move or otherwise change the flow of the water as you direct, up to 5 feet in any direction. This movement doesn’t have enough force to cause damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You cause the water to form into simple shapes and animate at your direction. This change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You change the water’s color or opacity. The water must be changed in the same way throughout. This change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You freeze the water, provided that there are no creatures in it. The water unfreezes in 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have no more than two of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You choose an area of water that you can see within range and that fits within a 5-foot cube. You manipulate it in one of the following ways:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>You instantaneously move or otherwise change the flow of the water as you direct, up to 5 feet in any direction. This movement doesn’t have enough force to cause damage.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You cause the water to form into simple shapes and animate at your direction. This change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You change the water’s color or opacity. The water must be changed in the same way throughout. This change lasts for 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>You freeze the water, provided that there are no creatures in it. The water unfreezes in 1 hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have no more than two of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 164","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":5,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickTemplate":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.PIeLZ0KrhJNHe9sc"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2397,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138229,"sources":[{"pageNumber":164,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/commodities/materials/liquid-droplet-blue.webp","name":"Shape Water","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"etMAXzXMvdQjDwij","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"a sapphire worth 1,000 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You touch an object weighing 10 pounds or less whose longest dimension is 6 feet or less. The spell leaves an invisible mark on its surface and invisibly inscribes the name of the item on the sapphire you use as the material component. Each time you cast this spell, you must use a different sapphire. <br /><br />At any time thereafter, you can use your action to speak the item’s name and crush the sapphire. The item instantly appears in your hand regardless of physical or planar distances, and the spell ends.</p>\n<p>If another creature is holding or carrying the item, crushing the sapphire doesn’t transport the item to you, but instead you learn who the creature possessing the object is and roughly where that creature is located at that moment. <br /><br />Dispel magic or a similar effect successfully applied to the sapphire ends this spell’s effect.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You touch an object weighing 10 pounds or less whose longest dimension is 6 feet or less. The spell leaves an invisible mark on its surface and invisibly inscribes the name of the item on the sapphire you use as the material component. Each time you cast this spell, you must use a different sapphire. <br /><br />At any time thereafter, you can use your action to speak the item’s name and crush the sapphire. The item instantly appears in your hand regardless of physical or planar distances, and the spell ends.</p>\n<p>If another creature is holding or carrying the item, crushing the sapphire doesn’t transport the item to you, but instead you learn who the creature possessing the object is and roughly where that creature is located at that moment. <br /><br />Dispel magic or a similar effect successfully applied to the sapphire ends this spell’s effect.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"unti","value":""},"formula":"","level":6,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":1000,"supply":0,"value":"a sapphire worth 1,000 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Player's Handbook pg 235","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.N43929xr0l5p8TXz"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2359,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136667,"sources":[{"pageNumber":235,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Teleportation","Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-flight-wings-purple.webp","name":"Drawmij's Instant Summons","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"evMIhzbvurIDKaxh","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"hour"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp and at least 1 cubic inch of flesh of the creature that is to be cloned, which the spell consumes, and a vessel worth at least 2,000 gp that has a sealable lid and is large enough to hold a Medium creature, such as a huge urn, coffin, mud- filled cyst in the ground, or crystal container filled with salt water","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>This spell grows an inert duplicate of a living, Medium creature as a safeguard against death. This clone forms inside a sealed vessel and grows to full size and maturity after 120 days; you can also choose to have the clone be a younger version of the same creature. It remains inert and endures indefinitely, as long as its vessel remains undisturbed.</p>\n<p>At any time after the clone matures, if the original creature dies, its soul transfers to the clone, provided that the soul is free and willing to return. The clone is physically identical to the original and has the same personality, memories, and abilities, but none of the original's equipment. The original creature's physical remains, if they still exist, become inert and can't thereafter be restored to life, since the creature's soul is elsewhere.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>This spell grows an inert duplicate of a living, Medium creature as a safeguard against death. This clone forms inside a sealed vessel and grows to full size and maturity after 120 days; you can also choose to have the clone be a younger version of the same creature. It remains inert and endures indefinitely, as long as its vessel remains undisturbed.</p>\n<p>At any time after the clone matures, if the original creature dies, its soul transfers to the clone, provided that the soul is free and willing to return. The clone is physically identical to the original and has the same personality, memories, and abilities, but none of the original's equipment. The original creature's physical remains, if they still exist, become inert and can't thereafter be restored to life, since the creature's soul is elsewhere.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":8,"materials":{"consumed":true,"cost":1000,"supply":0,"value":"a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp and at least 1 cubic inch of flesh of the creature that is to be cloned, which the spell consumes, and a vessel worth at least 2,000 gp that has a sealable lid and is large enough to hold a Medium creature, such as a huge urn, coffin, mud- filled cyst in the ground, or crystal container filled with salt water"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 222","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.UW5fK4luFXFPpi7f"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2029,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136216,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":222,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Utility"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/debuff-energy-hold-yellow.webp","name":"Clone","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"fBXe2BDQpNnvhpDz","name":"Blade Barrier","type":"spell","img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-beams-salvo-white.webp","data":{"description":{"value":"<p>You create a vertical wall of whirling, razor-sharp blades made of magical energy. The wall appears within range and lasts for the duration. You can make a straight wall up to 100 feet long, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick, or a ringed wall up to 60 feet in diameter, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick. The wall provides three-quarters cover to creatures behind it, and its space is difficult terrain.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the wall's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 6d10 slashing damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p>","chat":"<p>You create a vertical wall of whirling, razor-sharp blades made of magical energy. The wall appears within range and lasts for the duration. You can make a straight wall up to 100 feet long, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick, or a ringed wall up to 60 feet in diameter, 20 feet high, and 5 feet thick. The wall provides three-quarters cover to creatures behind it, and its space is difficult terrain.</p>\n<p>When a creature enters the wall's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes 6d10 slashing damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage.</p>","unidentified":""},"source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 218","activation":{"type":"action","cost":1,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":10,"units":"minute"},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":90,"long":null,"units":"ft"},"uses":{"value":0,"max":"0","per":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":"","amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["6d10","slashing"]],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"level":6,"school":"evo","components":{"value":"","vocal":true,"somatic":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"concentration":true},"materials":{"value":"","consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"scaling":{"mode":"none","formula":""}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true}},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.fM1bKCNV0vPTUF0M"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2015,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136117,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":218,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}}}
{"_id":"fHqp9GQDiNoxlsTR","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"Damage can't break concentration on this spell.","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a piece of tentacle from a giant octopus or a giant squid","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["3d6","bludgeoning"],["@classes.warlock.levels","temphp"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>Squirming, ebony tentacles fill a 20-foot square on ground that you can see within range. For the duration, these tentacles turn the ground in the area into difficult terrain. <br /><br />When a creature enters the affected area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 3d6 bludgeoning damage and be restrained by the tentacles until the spell ends. A creature that starts its turn in the area and is already restrained by the tentacles takes 3d6 bludgeoning damage. <br /><br />A creature restrained by the tentacles can use its action to make a Strength or Dexterity check (its choice) against your spell save DC. On a success, it frees itself.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>Squirming, ebony tentacles fill a 20-foot square on ground that you can see within range. For the duration, these tentacles turn the ground in the area into difficult terrain. <br /><br />When a creature enters the affected area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, the creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 3d6 bludgeoning damage and be restrained by the tentacles until the spell ends. A creature that starts its turn in the area and is already restrained by the tentacles takes 3d6 bludgeoning damage. <br /><br />A creature restrained by the tentacles can use its action to make a Strength or Dexterity check (its choice) against your spell save DC. On a success, it frees itself.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a piece of tentacle from a giant octopus or a giant squid"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":90},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Player's Handbook pg 238","target":{"type":"square","units":"ft","value":20,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"0","per":"","value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":"","1":""},"value":{"0":true,"1":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickTemplate":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.dQNUOwuZmkwvbg4p"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2344,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136739,"sources":[{"pageNumber":238,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/water/bubbles-air-water-light.webp","name":"Evard's Black Tentacles (Fathomless)","permission":{"OUGmAvuCIi3KewGn":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"fNsgsRPnSdQ0P6Ye","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"util","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a small amount of makeup applied to the face as this spell is cast","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>For the duration, you have advantage on all Charisma checks directed at one creature of your choice that isn’t hostile toward you. When the spell ends, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood and becomes hostile toward you. A creature prone to violence might attack you. Another creature might seek retribution in other ways (at the DM’s discretion), depending on the nature of your interaction with it.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>For the duration, you have advantage on all Charisma checks directed at one creature of your choice that isn’t hostile toward you. When the spell ends, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood and becomes hostile toward you. A creature prone to violence might attack you. Another creature might seek retribution in other ways (at the DM’s discretion), depending on the nature of your interaction with it.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a small amount of makeup applied to the face as this spell is cast"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"enc","source":"Player's Handbook pg 244","target":{"type":"self","units":"","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource"