{"_id":"fc6DGWL6ozvHdSiT","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"msak","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"reaction"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"Uses the damage type of the triggered attack: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Poison.","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6",""]],"value":"","versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The spell captures some of the incoming energy, lessening its effect on you and storing it for your next melee attack. You have resistance to the triggering damage type until the start of your next turn. Also, the first time you hit with a melee attack on your next turn, the target takes an extra 1d6 damage of the triggering type, and the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the extra damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The spell captures some of the incoming energy, lessening its effect on you and storing it for your next melee attack. You have resistance to the triggering damage type until the start of your next turn. Also, the first time you hit with a melee attack on your next turn, the target takes an extra 1d6 damage of the triggering type, and the spell ends.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the extra damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"round","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"level"},"school":"abj","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 150","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.Bp4atcCsTCoKIIkf"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2368,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137857,"sources":[{"pageNumber":150,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Warding"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/lightning/orb-ball-purple.webp","name":"Absorb Elements","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"fvhkvp0Lv5Slrnu4","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You take control of the air in a 100-foot cube that you can see within range. Choose one of the following effects when you cast the spell. The effect lasts for the spell’s duration, unless you use your action on a later turn to switch to a different effect. You can also use your action to temporarily halt the effect or to restart one you’ve halted.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Gusts.</span></strong> A wind picks up within the cube, continually blowing in a horizontal direction you designate. You choose the intensity of the wind: calm, moderate, or strong. If the wind is moderate or strong, ranged weapon attacks that enter or leave the cube or pass through it have disadvantage on their attack rolls. If the wind is strong, any creature moving against the wind must spend 1 extra foot of movement for each foot moved.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>Downdraft.</strong> </span>You cause a sustained blast of strong wind to blow downward from the top of the cube. Ranged weapon attacks that pass through the cube or that are made against targets within it have disadvantage on their attack rolls. A creature must make a Strength saving throw if it flies into the cube for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there flying. On a failed save, the creature is knocked prone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Updraft.</span></strong> You cause a sustained updraft within the cube, rising upward from the cube’s bottom side. Creatures that end a fall within the cube take only half damage from the fall. When a creature in the cube makes a vertical jump, the creature can jump up to 10 feet higher than normal.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You take control of the air in a 100-foot cube that you can see within range. Choose one of the following effects when you cast the spell. The effect lasts for the spell’s duration, unless you use your action on a later turn to switch to a different effect. You can also use your action to temporarily halt the effect or to restart one you’ve halted.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Gusts.</span></strong> A wind picks up within the cube, continually blowing in a horizontal direction you designate. You choose the intensity of the wind: calm, moderate, or strong. If the wind is moderate or strong, ranged weapon attacks that enter or leave the cube or pass through it have disadvantage on their attack rolls. If the wind is strong, any creature moving against the wind must spend 1 extra foot of movement for each foot moved.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>Downdraft.</strong> </span>You cause a sustained blast of strong wind to blow downward from the top of the cube. Ranged weapon attacks that pass through the cube or that are made against targets within it have disadvantage on their attack rolls. A creature must make a Strength saving throw if it flies into the cube for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there flying. On a failed save, the creature is knocked prone.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><strong><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\">Updraft.</span></strong> You cause a sustained updraft within the cube, rising upward from the cube’s bottom side. Creatures that end a fall within the cube take only half damage from the fall. When a creature in the cube makes a vertical jump, the creature can jump up to 10 feet higher than normal.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":300},"save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 152","target":{"type":"cube","units":"ft","value":100,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.6ezO2dz36sn9tE96"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2375,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137961,"sources":[{"pageNumber":152,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/air-wave-gust-blue.webp","name":"Control Winds","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"fwBCSAg7ntzlIDOs","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"bonus"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>This spell allows you to move at an incredible pace. When you cast this spell, and then as a bonus action on each of your turns until the spell ends, you can take the Dash action.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>This spell allows you to move at an incredible pace. When you cast this spell, and then as a bonus action on each of your turns until the spell ends, you can take the Dash action.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 238","target":{"type":"self","units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.0jeKIfSgul3stb1L"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2088,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136742,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":238,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Movement"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/wind-stream-blue-gray.webp","name":"Expeditious Retreat","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"g0y5JNseI1eKMv8k","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a forked, metal rod worth at least 250 gp, attuned to a particular plane of existence","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You and up to eight willing creatures who link hands in a circle are transported to a different plane of existence. You can specify a target destination in general terms, such as the City of Brass on the Elemental Plane of Fire or the palace of Dispater on the second level of the Nine Hells, and you appear in or near that destination. If you are trying to reach the City of Brass, for example, you might arrive in its Street of Steel, before its Gate of Ashes, or looking at the city from across the Sea of Fire, at the GM's discretion.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, if you know the sigil sequence of a teleportation circle on another plane of existence, this spell can take you to that circle. If the teleportation circle is too small to hold all the creatures you transported, they appear in the closest unoccupied spaces next to the circle.</p>\n<p>You can use this spell to banish an unwilling creature to another plane. Choose a creature within your reach and make a melee spell attack against it. On a hit, the creature must make a Charisma saving throw. If the creature fails this save, it is transported to a random location on the plane of existence you specify. A creature so transported must find its own way back to your current plane of existence.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You and up to eight willing creatures who link hands in a circle are transported to a different plane of existence. You can specify a target destination in general terms, such as the City of Brass on the Elemental Plane of Fire or the palace of Dispater on the second level of the Nine Hells, and you appear in or near that destination. If you are trying to reach the City of Brass, for example, you might arrive in its Street of Steel, before its Gate of Ashes, or looking at the city from across the Sea of Fire, at the GM's discretion.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, if you know the sigil sequence of a teleportation circle on another plane of existence, this spell can take you to that circle. If the teleportation circle is too small to hold all the creatures you transported, they appear in the closest unoccupied spaces next to the circle.</p>\n<p>You can use this spell to banish an unwilling creature to another plane. Choose a creature within your reach and make a melee spell attack against it. On a hit, the creature must make a Charisma saving throw. If the creature fails this save, it is transported to a random location on the plane of existence you specify. A creature so transported must find its own way back to your current plane of existence.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":250,"supply":0,"value":"a forked, metal rod worth at least 250 gp, attuned to a particular plane of existence"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"cha","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 266","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.96EdJVXepeXHcmXd"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2206,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138554,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":266,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Teleportation","Banishment"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange-purple.webp","name":"Plane Shift","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"g8WktFigoZ8LxWZ7","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["7d6","acid"],["7d6","cold"],["7d6","fire"],["7d6","lightning"],["7d6","necrotic"],["7d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">By gathering threads of shadow material from the Shadowfell, you create a Huge shadowy dragon in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. The illusion lasts for the spell’s duration and occupies its space, as if it were a creature.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">When the illusion appears, any of your enemies that can see it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become frightened of it for 1 minute. If a frightened creature ends its turn in a location where it doesn’t have line of sight to the illusion, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the illusion up to 60 feet. At any point during its movement, you can cause it to exhale a blast of energy in a 60-foot cone originating from its space. When you create the dragon, choose a damage type: acid, cold, fire, lightning, necrotic, or poison. Each creature in the cone must make an Intelligence saving throw, taking 7d6 damage of the chosen damage type on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The illusion is tangible because of the shadow stuff used to create it, but attacks miss it automatically, it succeeds on all saving throws, and it is immune to all damage and conditions. A creature that uses an action to examine the dragon can determine that it is an illusion by succeeding on an Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the creature can see through it and has advantage on saving throws against its breath.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">By gathering threads of shadow material from the Shadowfell, you create a Huge shadowy dragon in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. The illusion lasts for the spell’s duration and occupies its space, as if it were a creature.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">When the illusion appears, any of your enemies that can see it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or become frightened of it for 1 minute. If a frightened creature ends its turn in a location where it doesn’t have line of sight to the illusion, it can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the illusion up to 60 feet. At any point during its movement, you can cause it to exhale a blast of energy in a 60-foot cone originating from its space. When you create the dragon, choose a damage type: acid, cold, fire, lightning, necrotic, or poison. Each creature in the cone must make an Intelligence saving throw, taking 7d6 damage of the chosen damage type on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The illusion is tangible because of the shadow stuff used to create it, but attacks miss it automatically, it succeeds on all saving throws, and it is immune to all damage and conditions. A creature that uses an action to examine the dragon can determine that it is an illusion by succeeding on an Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the creature can see through it and has advantage on saving throws against its breath.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":8,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 157","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.1IxJCnuInGCaPlIa"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14876,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138120,"sources":[{"pageNumber":157,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Creation","Damage"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/creatures/reptiles/serpent-horned-green.webp","name":"Illusory Dragon","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"gEZwsjqMK2M76Y9Z","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Threads of dark power leap from your fingers to pierce up to five Small or Medium corpses you can see within range. Each corpse immediately stands up and becomes undead. You decide whether it is a zombie or a skeleton (the statistics for zombies and skeletons are in the <span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">Monster Manual</span>), and it gains a bonus to its attack and damage rolls equal to your spellcasting ability modifier.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You can use a bonus action to mentally command the creatures you make with this spell, issuing the same command to all of them. To receive the command, a creature must be within 60 feet of you. You decide what action the creatures will take and where they will move during their next turn, or you can issue a general command, such as to guard a chamber or passageway against your foes. If you issue no commands, the creatures do nothing except defend themselves against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the creatures continue to follow it until their task is complete.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The creatures are under your control until the spell ends, after which they become inanimate once more.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you animate up to two additional corpses for each slot level above 5th.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Threads of dark power leap from your fingers to pierce up to five Small or Medium corpses you can see within range. Each corpse immediately stands up and becomes undead. You decide whether it is a zombie or a skeleton (the statistics for zombies and skeletons are in the <span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Italic-Serif\">Monster Manual</span>), and it gains a bonus to its attack and damage rolls equal to your spellcasting ability modifier.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You can use a bonus action to mentally command the creatures you make with this spell, issuing the same command to all of them. To receive the command, a creature must be within 60 feet of you. You decide what action the creatures will take and where they will move during their next turn, or you can issue a general command, such as to guard a chamber or passageway against your foes. If you issue no commands, the creatures do nothing except defend themselves against hostile creatures. Once given an order, the creatures continue to follow it until their task is complete.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The creatures are under your control until the spell ends, after which they become inanimate once more.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\"><span class=\"Serif-Character-Style_Inline-Subhead-Serif\"><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> </span>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, you animate up to two additional corpses for each slot level above 5th.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"nec","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 153","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.OYHU5zvaKd2FAf84"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14830,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":137975,"sources":[{"pageNumber":153,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Creation","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/acid/dissolve-bone-ribs-skull.webp","name":"Danse Macabre","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"gbsxQzHTFiqbglJC","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":false,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You touch a willing beast. For the duration of the spell, you can use your action to see through the beast’s eyes and hear what it hears, and continue to do so until you use your action to return to your normal senses. While perceiving through the beast’s senses, you gain the benefits of any special senses possessed by that creature, though you are blinded and deafened to your own surroundings.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You touch a willing beast. For the duration of the spell, you can use your action to see through the beast’s eyes and hear what it hears, and continue to do so until you use your action to return to your normal senses. While perceiving through the beast’s senses, you gain the benefits of any special senses possessed by that creature, though you are blinded and deafened to your own surroundings.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"touch","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Player's Handbook pg 217","target":{"type":null,"units":"touch","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.n70WlrkAyN79goGI"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2325,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136108,"sources":[{"pageNumber":217,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/nature/wolf-paw-glow-purple-teal.webp","name":"Beast Sense","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"ggDsEs5A5CTLbBrL","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You speak a word of power that causes waves of intense pain to assail one creature you can see within range. If the target has 100 hit points or fewer, it is subject to crippling pain. Otherwise, the spell has no effect on it. A target is also unaffected if it is immune to being charmed.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">While the target is affected by crippling pain, any speed it has can be no higher than 10 feet. The target also has disadvantage on attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws, other than Constitution saving throws. Finally, if the target tries to cast a spell, it must first succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or the casting fails and the spell is wasted.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A target suffering this pain can make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. On a successful save, the pain ends.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You speak a word of power that causes waves of intense pain to assail one creature you can see within range. If the target has 100 hit points or fewer, it is subject to crippling pain. Otherwise, the spell has no effect on it. A target is also unaffected if it is immune to being charmed.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">While the target is affected by crippling pain, any speed it has can be no higher than 10 feet. The target also has disadvantage on attack rolls, ability checks, and saving throws, other than Constitution saving throws. Finally, if the target tries to cast a spell, it must first succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or the casting fails and the spell is wasted.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">A target suffering this pain can make a Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns. On a successful save, the pain ends.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"enc","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 163","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.yLUbvVJb59srRQ2p"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14520,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138210,"sources":[{"pageNumber":163,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Debuff"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/sonic/scream-wail-shout-teal.webp","name":"Power Word Pain","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"goGP9DNmKbbhMSu5","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":false,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["","radiant"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>A Large spectral guardian appears and hovers for the duration in an unoccupied space of your choice that you can see within range. The guardian occupies that space and is indistinct except for a gleaming sword and shield emblazoned with the symbol of your deity.</p>\n<p>Any creature hostile to you that moves to a space within 10 feet of the guardian for the first time on a turn must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw. The creature takes 20 radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The guardian vanishes when it has dealt a total of 60 damage.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>A Large spectral guardian appears and hovers for the duration in an unoccupied space of your choice that you can see within range. The guardian occupies that space and is indistinct except for a gleaming sword and shield emblazoned with the symbol of your deity.</p>\n<p>Any creature hostile to you that moves to a space within 10 feet of the guardian for the first time on a turn must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw. The creature takes 20 radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The guardian vanishes when it has dealt a total of 60 damage.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":8},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"dex","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 246","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.BP75IhalwUm0oszs"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2130,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138008,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":246,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/control/buff-flight-wings-runes-blue-white.webp","name":"Guardian of Faith","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"hCRJbaStMAjueIRj","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"humanoid blood inside a ruby vial worth at least 600 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You call forth a fiendish spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Fiendish Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose Demon, Devil, or Yugoloth. The creature resembles a fiend of the chosen type, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder stat-block-background\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Fiendish Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Large fiend</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 12 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 50 (Demon only) or 40 (Devil only) or 60 (Yugoloth only) + 15 for each spell level above 6th</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 40 ft.; climb 40 ft. (Demon only); fly 60 ft. (Devil only)</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">STR</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">13</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+1)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">DEX</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CON</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">15</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+2)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">INT</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">10</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">WIS</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">10</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CHA</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Damage Resistances </strong>fire</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Damage Immunities </strong>poison</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Condition Immunities </strong>poisoned</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Senses </strong>darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Languages </strong>Abyssal, Infernal, telepathy 60 ft.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data-Last\"><strong>Challenge</strong> — <strong>Proficiency Bonus</strong> equals your bonus</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Death Throes (Demon Only).</strong></em> When the fiend drops to 0 hit points or the spell ends, the fiend explodes, and each creature within 10 feet of it must make a Dexterity saving throw against your spell save DC. A creature takes 2d10 + this spell’s level fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Devil’s Sight (Devil Only).</strong></em> Magical darkness doesn’t impede the fiend’s darkvision.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Magic Resistance.</strong></em> The fiend has advantage on saving throws against spells and other magical effects.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Multiattack.</strong></em> The fiend makes a number of attacks equal to half this spell’s level (rounded down).</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Bite (Demon Only).</strong></em> <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d12 + 3 + the spell’s level necrotic damage.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Claws (Yugoloth Only).</strong></em> <em>Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d8 + 3 + the spell’s level slashing damage. Immediately after the attack hits or misses, the fiend can magically teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space it can see.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Hurl Flame (Devil Only).</strong></em> <em>Ranged Spell Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, range 150 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 2d6 + 3 + the spell’s level fire damage. If the target is a flammable object that isn’t being worn or carried, it also catches fire.</p>\n</div>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You call forth a fiendish spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Fiendish Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose Demon, Devil, or Yugoloth. The creature resembles a fiend of the chosen type, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 7th level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder stat-block-background\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Fiendish Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Large fiend</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 12 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 50 (Demon only) or 40 (Devil only) or 60 (Yugoloth only) + 15 for each spell level above 6th</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 40 ft.; climb 40 ft. (Demon only); fly 60 ft. (Devil only)</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability