{"_id":"qWvU55OtPCBcZzEM","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a living flea","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["1d6","poison"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You cause a cloud of mites, fleas, and other parasites to appear momentarily on one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or it takes 1d6 poison damage and moves 5 feet in a random direction if it can move and its speed is at least 5 feet. Roll a d4 for the direction: 1, north; 2, south; 3, east; or 4, west. This movement doesn’t provoke opportunity attacks, and if the direction rolled is blocked, the target doesn’t move.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The spell’s damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You cause a cloud of mites, fleas, and other parasites to appear momentarily on one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or it takes [[/r 1d6]] poison damage and moves 5 feet in a random direction if it can move and its speed is at least 5 feet. Roll a [[/r d4]] for the direction: 1, north; 2, south; 3, east; or 4, west. This movement doesn’t provoke opportunity attacks, and if the direction rolled is blocked, the target doesn’t move.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The spell’s damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":null},"formula":"","level":0,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a living flea"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"con","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"1d6","mode":"cantrip"},"school":"con","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 158","target":{"type":"creature","units":"","value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"","per":"","value":null}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDamage":{"context":{"0":""},"value":{"0":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.MmRY2BUcvGBXXDmw"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14878,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138125,"sources":[{"pageNumber":158,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning","Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/creatures/invertebrates/fly-wasp-mosquito-green.webp","name":"Infestation","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"qcEgiHhbkTMhtriJ","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a bit of bat fur","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You create an invisible, magical eye within range that hovers in the air for the duration.</p>\n<p>You mentally receive visual information from the eye, which has normal vision and darkvision out to 30 feet. The eye can look in every direction.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can move the eye up to 30 feet in any direction. There is no limit to how far away from you the eye can move, but it can't enter another plane of existence. A solid barrier blocks the eye's movement, but the eye can pass through an opening as small as 1 inch in diameter.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You create an invisible, magical eye within range that hovers in the air for the duration.</p>\n<p>You mentally receive visual information from the eye, which has normal vision and darkvision out to 30 feet. The eye can look in every direction.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can move the eye up to 30 feet in any direction. There is no limit to how far away from you the eye can move, but it can't enter another plane of existence. A solid barrier blocks the eye's movement, but the eye can pass through an opening as small as 1 inch in diameter.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":4,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a bit of bat fur"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 214","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.102NyFj0hNbRTzIt"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2001,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136058,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":214,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-teal.webp","name":"Arcane Eye","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"qg1713ZgwA33GjbZ","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":true,"ritual":true,"somatic":true,"value":"a drop of mercury","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>This spell creates a circular, horizontal plane of force, 3 feet in diameter and 1 inch thick, that floats 3 feet above the ground in an unoccupied space of your choice that you can see within range. The disk remains for the duration, and can hold up to 500 pounds. If more weight is placed on it, the spell ends, and everything on the disk falls to the ground.</p>\n<p>The disk is immobile while you are within 20 feet of it. If you move more than 20 feet away from it, the disk follows you so that it remains within 20 feet of you. It can move across uneven terrain, up or down stairs, slopes and the like, but it can't cross an elevation change of 10 feet or more. For example, the disk can't move across a 10-foot-deep pit, nor could it leave such a pit if it was created at the bottom.</p>\n<p>If you move more than 100 feet from the disk (typically because it can't move around an obstacle to follow you), the spell ends.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>This spell creates a circular, horizontal plane of force, 3 feet in diameter and 1 inch thick, that floats 3 feet above the ground in an unoccupied space of your choice that you can see within range. The disk remains for the duration, and can hold up to 500 pounds. If more weight is placed on it, the spell ends, and everything on the disk falls to the ground.</p>\n<p>The disk is immobile while you are within 20 feet of it. If you move more than 20 feet away from it, the disk follows you so that it remains within 20 feet of you. It can move across uneven terrain, up or down stairs, slopes and the like, but it can't cross an elevation change of 10 feet or more. For example, the disk can't move across a 10-foot-deep pit, nor could it leave such a pit if it was created at the bottom.</p>\n<p>If you move more than 100 feet from the disk (typically because it can't move around an obstacle to follow you), the spell ends.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":1,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a drop of mercury"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.lCx0W0hqAq7d4wt6"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2110,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":2307,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Movement","Utility"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-triangle-blue.webp","name":"Floating Disk","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"qm3AAU0E0nQuJTDs","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a caterpillar cocoon","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You transform up to ten creatures of your choice that you can see within range. An unwilling target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw to resist the transformation. An unwilling shapechanger automatically succeeds on the save.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Each target assumes a beast form of your choice, and you can choose the same form or different ones for each target. The new form can be any beast you have seen whose challenge rating is equal to or less than the target’s (or half the target’s level, if the target doesn’t have a challenge rating). The target’s game statistics, including mental ability scores, are replaced by the statistics of the chosen beast, but the target retains its hit points, alignment, and personality.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Each target gains a number of temporary hit points equal to the hit points of its new form. These temporary hit points can’t be replaced by temporary hit points from another source. A target reverts to its normal form when it has no more temporary hit points or it dies. If the spell ends before then, the creature loses all its temporary hit points and reverts to its normal form.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The creature is limited in the actions it can perform by the nature of its new form. It can’t speak, cast spells, or do anything else that requires hands or speech.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The target’s gear melds into the new form. The target can’t activate, use, wield, or otherwise benefit from any of its equipment.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">You transform up to ten creatures of your choice that you can see within range. An unwilling target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw to resist the transformation. An unwilling shapechanger automatically succeeds on the save.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Each target assumes a beast form of your choice, and you can choose the same form or different ones for each target. The new form can be any beast you have seen whose challenge rating is equal to or less than the target’s (or half the target’s level, if the target doesn’t have a challenge rating). The target’s game statistics, including mental ability scores, are replaced by the statistics of the chosen beast, but the target retains its hit points, alignment, and personality.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">Each target gains a number of temporary hit points equal to the hit points of its new form. These temporary hit points can’t be replaced by temporary hit points from another source. A target reverts to its normal form when it has no more temporary hit points or it dies. If the spell ends before then, the creature loses all its temporary hit points and reverts to its normal form.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The creature is limited in the actions it can perform by the nature of its new form. It can’t speak, cast spells, or do anything else that requires hands or speech.</p>\n<p class=\"Core-Styles_Core-Body\">The target’s gear melds into the new form. The target can’t activate, use, wield, or otherwise benefit from any of its equipment.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":9,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a caterpillar cocoon"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":120},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Xanathar's Guide to Everything pg 160","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":10,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.jBk3Cd4Bym5aOHyA"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":14882,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138190,"sources":[{"pageNumber":160,"sourceId":27,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control","Shapechanging"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/creatures/abilities/dragon-breath-purple.webp","name":"Mass Polymorph","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"qn6hNMpcSOsTqpuN","data":{"ability":"","actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":10,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a focus worth at least 1,000 gp, such as a crystal ball, a silver mirror, or a font filled with holy water","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":"","type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You can see and hear a particular creature you choose that is on the same plane of existence as you. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, which is modified by how well you know the target and the sort of physical connection you have to it. If a target knows you're casting this spell, it can fail the saving throw voluntarily if it wants to be observed.</p>\n<table style=\"height:114px\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>\n<p>Knowledge</p>\n</th>\n<th>Save Modifier</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Secondhand (you have heard of the target)</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Firsthand (you have met the target)</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Familiar (you know the target well)</td>\n<td>-5</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Connection</th>\n<th>Save Modifier</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Likeness or picture</td>\n<td>-2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Possession or garment</td>\n<td>-4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Body part, lock of hair, bit of nail, or the like</td>\n<td>-10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p>On a successful save, the target isn't affected, and you can't use this spell against it again for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>On a failed save, the spell creates an invisible sensor within 10 feet of the target. You can see and hear through the sensor as if you were there. The sensor moves with the target, remaining within 10 feet of it for the duration. A creature that can see invisible objects sees the sensor as a luminous orb about the size of your fist.</p>\n<p>Instead of targeting a creature, you can choose a location you have seen before as the target of this spell. When you do, the sensor appears at that location and doesn't move.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You can see and hear a particular creature you choose that is on the same plane of existence as you. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw, which is modified by how well you know the target and the sort of physical connection you have to it. If a target knows you're casting this spell, it can fail the saving throw voluntarily if it wants to be observed.</p>\n<table style=\"height:114px\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>\n<p>Knowledge</p>\n</th>\n<th>Save Modifier</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Secondhand (you have heard of the target)</td>\n<td>+5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Firsthand (you have met the target)</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Familiar (you know the target well)</td>\n<td>-5</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Connection</th>\n<th>Save Modifier</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Likeness or picture</td>\n<td>-2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Possession or garment</td>\n<td>-4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Body part, lock of hair, bit of nail, or the like</td>\n<td>-10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p>On a successful save, the target isn't affected, and you can't use this spell against it again for 24 hours.</p>\n<p>On a failed save, the spell creates an invisible sensor within 10 feet of the target. You can see and hear through the sensor as if you were there. The sensor moves with the target, remaining within 10 feet of it for the duration. A creature that can see invisible objects sees the sensor as a luminous orb about the size of your fist.</p>\n<p>Instead of targeting a creature, you can choose a location you have seen before as the target of this spell. When you do, the sensor appears at that location and doesn't move.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":10},"formula":"","level":5,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":1000,"supply":0,"value":"a focus worth at least 1,000 gp, such as a crystal ball, a silver mirror, or a font filled with holy water"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"self","value":null},"save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"div","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 273","target":{"type":"self","units":"","value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":"0","per":"","value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickDesc":{"value":true},"quickFlavor":{"value":true},"quickOther":{"context":"","value":true},"quickProperties":{"value":true},"quickSave":{"value":true},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true,"value":false}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.YKY381S1h3If31XE"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2239,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138669,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":273,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Detection"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-ringed-glow-angry-large-teal.webp","name":"Scrying","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"qzCMHRRIfwfGUz3W","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":10,"type":"minute"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You make terrain in an area up to 1 mile square look, sound, smell, and even feel like some other sort of terrain. The terrain's general shape remains the same, however. Open fields or a road could be made to resemble a swamp, hill, crevasse, or some other difficult or impassable terrain. A pond can be made to seem like a grassy meadow, a precipice like a gentle slope, or a rock-strewn gully like a wide and smooth road.</p>\n<p>Similarly, you can alter the appearance of structures, or add them where none are present. The spell doesn't disguise, conceal, or add creatures.</p>\n<p>The illusion includes audible, visual, tactile, and olfactory elements, so it can turn clear ground into difficult terrain (or vice versa) or otherwise impede movement through the area. Any piece of the illusory terrain (such as a rock or stick) that is removed from the spell's area disappears immediately.</p>\n<p>Creatures with truesight can see through the illusion to the terrain's true form; however, all other elements of the illusion remain, so while the creature is aware of the illusion's presence, the creature can still physically interact with the illusion.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You make terrain in an area up to 1 mile square look, sound, smell, and even feel like some other sort of terrain. The terrain's general shape remains the same, however. Open fields or a road could be made to resemble a swamp, hill, crevasse, or some other difficult or impassable terrain. A pond can be made to seem like a grassy meadow, a precipice like a gentle slope, or a rock-strewn gully like a wide and smooth road.</p>\n<p>Similarly, you can alter the appearance of structures, or add them where none are present. The spell doesn't disguise, conceal, or add creatures.</p>\n<p>The illusion includes audible, visual, tactile, and olfactory elements, so it can turn clear ground into difficult terrain (or vice versa) or otherwise impede movement through the area. Any piece of the illusory terrain (such as a rock or stick) that is removed from the spell's area disappears immediately.</p>\n<p>Creatures with truesight can see through the illusion to the terrain's true form; however, all other elements of the illusion remain, so while the creature is aware of the illusion's presence, the creature can still physically interact with the illusion.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"day","value":10},"formula":"","level":7,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"special","value":null},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"ill","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 260","target":{"type":"square","units":"ft","value":5280,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.9EdiiAFQlbMXGBns"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2192,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138491,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":260,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/air/fog-gas-smoke-swirling-blue.webp","name":"Mirage Arcane","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"r8HkDel2mL0034Ag","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"reaction"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":false,"material":false,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"","vocal":false},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, its spell fails and has no effect. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a success, the creature's spell fails and has no effect.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the interrupted spell has no effect if its level is less than or equal to the level of the spell slot you used.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You attempt to interrupt a creature in the process of casting a spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, its spell fails and has no effect. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an ability check using your spellcasting ability. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a success, the creature's spell fails and has no effect.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th level or higher, the interrupted spell has no effect if its level is less than or equal to the level of the spell slot you used.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"inst","value":""},"formula":"","level":3,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":""},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":60},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"abj","source":"Basic Rules, Player's Handbook pg 228","target":{"type":"creature","units":null,"value":1,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.iUv8XyQUZBDfyt7T"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2051,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":136448,"sources":[{"pageNumber":null,"sourceId":1,"sourceType":2},{"pageNumber":228,"sourceId":2,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Negation"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/skills/melee/strike-blade-hooked-orange-blue.webp","name":"Counterspell","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"rFB5i3sPCwoR5Q7Q","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"save","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a miniature hand sculpted from clay","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[["2d6","bludgeoning"],["2d6","bludgeoning"]],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You choose a 5-foot-square unoccupied space on the ground that you can see within range. A Medium hand made from compacted soil rises there and reaches for one creature you can see within 5 feet of it. The target must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage and is restrained for the spell’s duration.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can cause the hand to crush the restrained target, who must make a Strength saving throw. It takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>To break out, the restrained target can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target escapes and is no longer restrained by the hand.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can cause the hand to reach for a different creature or to move to a different unoccupied space within range. The hand releases a restrained target if you do either.</p>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You choose a 5-foot-square unoccupied space on the ground that you can see within range. A Medium hand made from compacted soil rises there and reaches for one creature you can see within 5 feet of it. The target must make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, the target takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage and is restrained for the spell’s duration.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can cause the hand to crush the restrained target, who must make a Strength saving throw. It takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>To break out, the restrained target can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target escapes and is no longer restrained by the hand.</p>\n<p>As an action, you can cause the hand to reach for a different creature or to move to a different unoccupied space within range. The hand releases a restrained target if you do either.</p>"},"duration":{"units":"minute","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":0,"supply":0,"value":"a miniature hand sculpted from clay"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":30},"save":{"ability":"str","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"trs","source":"Elemental Evil Player's Companion pg 161","target":{"type":"square","units":"ft","value":5,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.njnxXH7UBZ7KWBkB"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":2392,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":138192,"sources":[{"pageNumber":161,"sourceId":4,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Damage","Control"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/magic/earth/lava-explosion-orange.webp","name":"Maximilian's Earthen Grasp","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
{"_id":"rPGnNfF9AHP9YhOI","data":{"ability":null,"actionType":"other","activation":{"condition":"","cost":1,"type":"action"},"attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","components":{"concentration":true,"material":true,"ritual":false,"somatic":true,"value":"a feather, tuft of fur, and fish tail inside a gilded acorn worth at least 200 gp","vocal":true},"consume":{"amount":null,"target":null,"type":""},"critical":null,"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"description":{"chat":"<p>You call forth a bestial spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Bestial Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose an environment: Air, Land, or Water. The creature resembles an animal of your choice that is native to the chosen environment, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Bestial Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Small beast</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 11 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 20 (Air only) or 30 (Land and Water only) + 5 for each spell level above 2nd</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.; climb 30 ft. (Land only); fly 60 ft. (Air only); swim 30 ft. (Water only)</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">STR</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">18</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+4)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">DEX</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">11</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CON</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">INT</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">4</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">WIS</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">14</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+2)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CHA</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">5</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Languages</strong> understands the languages you speak</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data-Last\"><strong>Challenge</strong> — <strong>Proficiency Bonus</strong> equals your bonus</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Flyby (Air Only).</strong></em> The beast doesn’t provoke opportunity attacks when it flies out of an enemy’s reach.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Pack Tactics (Land and Water Only).</strong></em> The beast has advantage on an attack roll against a creature if at least one of the beast’s allies is within 5 feet of the creature and the ally isn’t incapacitated.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Water Breathing (Water Only).</strong></em> The beast can breathe only underwater.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Multiattack.</strong></em> The beast makes a number of attacks equal to half this spell’s level (rounded down).</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Maul.</strong> Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d8 + 4 + the spell’s level piercing damage.</p>\n</div>","unidentified":"","value":"<p>You call forth a bestial spirit. It manifests in an unoccupied space that you can see within range. This corporeal form uses the Bestial Spirit stat block. When you cast the spell, choose an environment: Air, Land, or Water. The creature resembles an animal of your choice that is native to the chosen environment, which determines certain traits in its stat block. The creature disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.</p>\n<p>The creature is an ally to you and your companions. In combat, the creature shares your initiative count, but it takes its turn immediately after yours. It obeys your verbal commands (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any, it takes the Dodge action and uses its move to avoid danger.</p>\n<p><em><strong>At Higher Levels.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, use the higher level wherever the spell’s level appears in the stat block.</p>\n<div class=\"Basic-Text-Frame stat-block-finder\">\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Title\">Bestial Spirit</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Metadata\">Small beast</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Armor Class</strong> 11 + the level of the spell (natural armor)</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Hit Points</strong> 20 (Air only) or 30 (Land and Water only) + 5 for each spell level above 2nd</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Speed</strong> 30 ft.; climb 30 ft. (Land only); fly 60 ft. (Air only); swim 30 ft. (Water only)</p>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">STR</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">18</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+4)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">DEX</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">11</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+0)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CON</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">16</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">INT</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">4</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">WIS</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">14</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(+2)</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-stat\">\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-heading\">CHA</div>\n<div class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-data\"><span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-score\">5</span> <span class=\"stat-block-ability-scores-modifier\">(−3)</span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data\"><strong>Languages</strong> understands the languages you speak</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Data-Last\"><strong>Challenge</strong> — <strong>Proficiency Bonus</strong> equals your bonus</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Flyby (Air Only).</strong></em> The beast doesn’t provoke opportunity attacks when it flies out of an enemy’s reach.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Pack Tactics (Land and Water Only).</strong></em> The beast has advantage on an attack roll against a creature if at least one of the beast’s allies is within 5 feet of the creature and the ally isn’t incapacitated.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Water Breathing (Water Only).</strong></em> The beast can breathe only underwater.</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Heading\">Actions</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Multiattack.</strong></em> The beast makes a number of attacks equal to half this spell’s level (rounded down).</p>\n<p class=\"Stat-Block-Styles_Stat-Block-Body\"><em><strong>Maul.</strong> Melee Weapon Attack:</em> your spell attack modifier to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. <em>Hit:</em> 1d8 + 4 + the spell’s level piercing damage.</p>\n</div>"},"duration":{"units":"hour","value":1},"formula":"","level":2,"materials":{"consumed":false,"cost":200,"supply":0,"value":"a feather, tuft of fur, and fish tail inside a gilded acorn worth at least 200 gp"},"preparation":{"mode":"prepared","prepared":false},"range":{"long":null,"units":"ft","value":90},"save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"spell"},"scaling":{"formula":"","mode":"none"},"school":"con","source":"Tasha’s Cauldron of Everything pg 109","target":{"type":null,"units":null,"value":null,"width":null},"uses":{"max":0,"per":null,"value":0}},"effects":[],"flags":{"betterRolls5e":{"quickCharges":{"altValue":{"resource":true,"use":true},"value":{"resource":true,"use":true}},"quickVersatile":{"altValue":true}},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.ddb-import-haven-spells.nyqU5hmakaOintHK"},"ddbimporter":{"definitionId":721187,"dndbeyond":{"castAtLevel":null,"level":null,"lookup":"generic","lookupName":"generic"},"entityTypeId":435869154,"id":5854852,"sources":[{"pageNumber":109,"sourceId":67,"sourceType":1}],"tags":["Summoning"]}},"folder":null,"img":"icons/commodities/claws/claw-bear-brown-grey.webp","name":"Summon Beast","permission":{"3AYHMWdZOlxF9nZC":3,"default":0},"sort":0,"type":"spell"}
